1
00:00:01,000 --> 00:00:02,401
Now, first,

2
00:00:02,401 --> 00:00:05,438
we will announce the winner...

3
00:00:05,438 --> 00:00:09,242
who took first place
with a total of 556 points.

4
00:00:11,136 --> 00:00:13,837
(21st place in Round 1)

5
00:00:14,080 --> 00:00:16,882
(2nd place in Round 2)

6
00:00:17,550 --> 00:00:19,886
(Even in Round 4,
where he sharpened his skills,)

7
00:00:21,454 --> 00:00:24,223
(he placed second, behind Hwang Ji Oh.)

8
00:00:25,691 --> 00:00:27,493
(Will Gyeong Mu's Sushi Bread Set...)

9
00:00:27,793 --> 00:00:29,829
(be able to break the jinx?)

10
00:00:30,329 --> 00:00:32,331
(A gift of "rest" for his mother)

11
00:00:34,066 --> 00:00:38,304
(Shaped like Jeju Island's basalt)

12
00:00:40,072 --> 00:00:43,609
(Expressing the sea
where his diver mother works)

13
00:00:44,710 --> 00:00:47,780
(Will Si Yeop's Mom's Place...)

14
00:00:48,481 --> 00:00:50,616
(be able to take 1st place?)

15
00:00:51,450 --> 00:00:56,176
Who will be the winner...

16
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:57,823
with 556 points?

17
00:00:58,190 --> 00:01:00,360
Will it be Gyeong Mu or Si Yeop?

18
00:01:01,060 --> 00:01:03,329
Si Yeop or Gyeong Mu?

19
00:01:03,896 --> 00:01:04,897
We will...

20
00:01:08,801 --> 00:01:10,336
reveal it now.

21
00:01:10,803 --> 00:01:14,307
The winner of Final Round One is...

22
00:01:15,708 --> 00:01:18,878
(Who is the winner of Final Round 1?)

23
00:01:25,184 --> 00:01:28,454
Jeju Blue Ribbon Winner, Kim Si Yeop.

24
00:01:28,454 --> 00:01:29,622
Congratulations!

25
00:01:30,389 --> 00:01:32,391
(Final Round 1 Winner with 556 points,
Kim Si Yeop)

26
00:01:32,391 --> 00:01:33,217
Thank you.

27
00:01:33,241 --> 00:01:34,493
Yes, congratulations.

28
00:01:49,141 --> 00:01:50,209
He truly deserves it.

29
00:01:50,573 --> 00:01:54,010
I didn't show it, but I feel amazing.

30
00:01:54,343 --> 00:01:57,713
I'll keep this momentum going
and beat everyone else...

31
00:01:57,713 --> 00:02:00,049
to become the ultimate winner.

32
00:02:03,085 --> 00:02:06,559
Competing against Si Yeop, I realized...

33
00:02:06,689 --> 00:02:09,525
that no one is more sincere
about pastries than he is.

34
00:02:09,559 --> 00:02:12,061
With his current flow and mindset,

35
00:02:12,562 --> 00:02:15,501
I think first place is in the bag.

36
00:02:15,731 --> 00:02:21,237
That means, naturally, Dessert Macho,
Lee Gyeong Mu takes second.

37
00:02:21,237 --> 00:02:23,042
(Final Round 1, 2nd place with 542 points,
Lee Gyeong Mu)

38
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:27,476
The best part about being number two is
that there's still room to climb.

39
00:02:27,910 --> 00:02:29,315
Well said!

40
00:02:31,581 --> 00:02:32,582
So cool.

41
00:02:33,149 --> 00:02:35,718
And that brings us to the final mission,
Round Two.

42
00:02:35,718 --> 00:02:36,822
Everyone, prepare yourselves.

43
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:39,124
He's so impressive.

44
00:02:41,060 --> 00:02:42,094
Truly cool.

45
00:02:43,293 --> 00:02:45,061
He's come a long way to get here.

46
00:02:45,061 --> 00:02:46,832
The finish line is in sight.

47
00:02:47,022 --> 00:02:50,504
He should give it his all
until the very end...

48
00:02:50,536 --> 00:02:51,937
and claim the throne.

49
00:02:52,101 --> 00:02:53,970
(Final Round 1 Ranking Announcement)

50
00:02:53,970 --> 00:02:57,707
(Si Yeop, Gyeong Mu, Hwa Young,
Ji Oh, Yeong Seok, Jin Seo, Min Su)

51
00:02:58,407 --> 00:03:02,211
The fierce journey of Bake Your Dream...

52
00:03:02,211 --> 00:03:04,513
is racing toward its conclusion.

53
00:03:05,047 --> 00:03:07,617
The results of Final Round One are in,

54
00:03:07,617 --> 00:03:10,586
but these ranking aren't the final word.

55
00:03:11,187 --> 00:03:13,189
Defending your spot,

56
00:03:13,589 --> 00:03:15,358
taking someone else's,

57
00:03:15,825 --> 00:03:17,994
or a total comeback,
it's all on the table.

58
00:03:21,698 --> 00:03:23,399
This is truly the end.

59
00:03:26,603 --> 00:03:28,238
To determine the single pastry...

60
00:03:28,238 --> 00:03:30,873
that will conquer the world.

61
00:03:31,874 --> 00:03:34,510
The final stage of Bake Your Dream.

62
00:03:34,810 --> 00:03:37,511
The final battleground, Round Two.

63
00:03:37,512 --> 00:03:40,019
Only one match remains.

64
00:03:40,449 --> 00:03:44,690
After a three-month journey
of intense competition,

65
00:03:44,690 --> 00:03:45,988
(Round 3, A Twist on the Classics:
16 contestants)

66
00:03:45,988 --> 00:03:46,989
(Round 4, Local Heritage: 10 contestants)

67
00:03:46,989 --> 00:03:47,990
(Final Round Top 7)

68
00:03:47,990 --> 00:03:50,296
the winner who will lift the trophy...

69
00:03:50,321 --> 00:03:51,936
and those who will taste
the bitterness of defeat...

70
00:03:51,961 --> 00:03:54,266
will be revealed here today.

71
00:03:55,432 --> 00:03:56,532
Also, today,

72
00:03:56,556 --> 00:04:00,201
to celebrate the crowning of our champion,

73
00:04:00,202 --> 00:04:05,207
the colleagues who shared
their sweat and tears are back with us.

74
00:04:05,374 --> 00:04:09,245
(Familiar faces
we haven't seen in a while)

75
00:04:09,412 --> 00:04:10,947
Let's go!

76
00:04:12,818 --> 00:04:14,984
Si Yeop, keep it up!

77
00:04:15,618 --> 00:04:17,086
- Go, Hwang Ji Oh!
- You've got this!

78
00:04:19,055 --> 00:04:23,028
The final mission consists of two rounds.

79
00:04:23,659 --> 00:04:27,697
By combining the scores
from Rounds 1 and 2,

80
00:04:27,697 --> 00:04:31,500
the ultimate winner
of Bake Your Dream will be decided.

81
00:04:32,442 --> 00:04:34,545
Depending on the results of this round,

82
00:04:34,570 --> 00:04:36,873
the rankings could flip completely.

83
00:04:37,649 --> 00:04:40,017
The Final Round Two mission...

84
00:04:40,042 --> 00:04:41,344
(What is the theme for Final Round 2?)

85
00:04:41,344 --> 00:04:42,478
will be revealed now.

86
00:04:44,088 --> 00:04:47,825
(Final Round 2: The Ultimate Pastry)

87
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:50,853
Create the one pastry...

88
00:04:50,853 --> 00:04:53,159
that will conquer the world,
the Ultimate Pastry.

89
00:04:53,857 --> 00:04:57,360
All the skills and experiences
from this journey,

90
00:04:57,385 --> 00:05:00,721
and your own story, must be distilled
into a single creation.

91
00:05:00,830 --> 00:05:03,432
You must create the one pastry...

92
00:05:03,432 --> 00:05:06,035
that will engrave your name
on the world stage.

93
00:05:06,869 --> 00:05:10,640
The time limit for Final Round 2
is 4 hours.

94
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:11,777
(Time limit: 4 hours)

95
00:05:13,012 --> 00:05:14,046
It's an open theme.

96
00:05:14,755 --> 00:05:15,719
That's going to be tough.

97
00:05:15,744 --> 00:05:16,712
(Anything is possible in Round 2.)

98
00:05:17,316 --> 00:05:19,922
I'm confident
in the "Ultimate Pastry" theme...

99
00:05:19,947 --> 00:05:24,287
because I wanted to blend what I love...

100
00:05:24,312 --> 00:05:28,027
with something
the Masters can connect with.

101
00:05:28,558 --> 00:05:30,693
I'm even more confident in Round Two.

102
00:05:30,860 --> 00:05:32,128
I'll prove it.

103
00:05:33,229 --> 00:05:36,502
I didn't hesitate for a second.
The idea came to me instantly.

104
00:05:37,700 --> 00:05:39,068
Since it's the final,

105
00:05:39,268 --> 00:05:43,572
some incredible Special Masters
are joining us.

106
00:05:43,573 --> 00:05:46,442
(Three Special Masters)

107
00:05:47,476 --> 00:05:50,012
(Special Master Kim Yeong Mo)

108
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,982
(A living legend
in the Korean pastry world)

109
00:05:53,082 --> 00:05:55,818
(Started in a 20-square-meter bakery
in 1982)

110
00:05:56,452 --> 00:05:59,455
(Led the pastry industry
for over 40 years)

111
00:05:59,855 --> 00:06:02,561
(The 6th Pastry Master of Korea,
Kim Yeong Mo)

112
00:06:02,561 --> 00:06:04,551
Based on the belief...

113
00:06:04,575 --> 00:06:07,062
that the most Korean thing
is the most global,

114
00:06:07,429 --> 00:06:13,772
I'll be looking at how well Korean beauty
and flavor are expressed.

115
00:06:16,272 --> 00:06:18,006
In all my years in this industry,

116
00:06:18,006 --> 00:06:23,616
I never imagined
I'd meet Master Kim in person.

117
00:06:24,080 --> 00:06:26,619
He's like the president
of the pastry world.

118
00:06:27,386 --> 00:06:30,920
Being evaluated
by someone of his stature...

119
00:06:31,419 --> 00:06:32,891
is such an honor.

120
00:06:33,035 --> 00:06:34,460
I'm really excited.

121
00:06:35,225 --> 00:06:38,230
Next is Master Julien Perrinet.

122
00:06:39,195 --> 00:06:41,864
(One of the world's Top 400 Chefs,
2019 The Best Chef Awards)

123
00:06:41,865 --> 00:06:42,923
(Founding member...)

124
00:06:42,947 --> 00:06:45,535
(of the 2 and 3-star Michelin
Joël Robuchon restaurants in Singapore)

125
00:06:45,601 --> 00:06:49,305
(Current Executive Pastry Chef
for Hyatt Asia)

126
00:06:49,472 --> 00:06:52,174
(Chef Julien Perrinet)

127
00:06:52,176 --> 00:06:57,528
I'll be looking for something
I've never seen before,

128
00:06:57,552 --> 00:06:59,207
something truly creative.

129
00:06:59,232 --> 00:07:03,755
Most importantly for me, I'm looking
for a taste I can't wait to try,

130
00:07:03,756 --> 00:07:05,825
and taste your creations.

131
00:07:06,421 --> 00:07:07,456
Good luck to everyone.

132
00:07:12,328 --> 00:07:15,401
Next is Master Davide Cardellini.

133
00:07:16,265 --> 00:07:18,568
(Chef from a 2-star Michelin restaurant)

134
00:07:18,801 --> 00:07:22,171
(Collaborated with world-renowned chef
Massimo Bottura)

135
00:07:22,171 --> 00:07:25,141
(Current Executive Chef
at Hilton Hotel Gyeongju)

136
00:07:25,274 --> 00:07:28,044
(Chef Davide Cardellini)

137
00:07:28,637 --> 00:07:33,279
Today, my criteria will be
precision and technique.

138
00:07:33,776 --> 00:07:36,217
To me, beauty is very important.

139
00:07:36,242 --> 00:07:41,315
An aesthetic message in your choice
of ingredients and your storytelling,

140
00:07:41,355 --> 00:07:44,193
one that is harmonious and delicious.

141
00:07:50,367 --> 00:07:52,705
Who will take home the grand prize
of 100,000 dollars,

142
00:07:53,169 --> 00:07:54,770
a new brand launch,

143
00:07:55,104 --> 00:07:57,807
and a premium electric SUV,

144
00:07:57,807 --> 00:08:01,510
to become the sole winner
of Bake Your Dream?

145
00:08:02,912 --> 00:08:05,181
My goal is first place.

146
00:08:06,215 --> 00:08:07,783
Since I've made it this far,

147
00:08:08,384 --> 00:08:09,688
It has to be first.

148
00:08:10,253 --> 00:08:12,622
I really want to reach the top.

149
00:08:13,017 --> 00:08:14,126
I'll give it my everything.

150
00:08:14,589 --> 00:08:17,193
I'm going to win and take that prize.

151
00:08:18,461 --> 00:08:19,729
The win is mine.

152
00:08:20,630 --> 00:08:22,901
Then, let us begin...

153
00:08:23,632 --> 00:08:24,800
the final competition!

154
00:08:29,705 --> 00:08:32,742
- Hwang Ji Oh is unstoppable!
- Go for it!

155
00:08:37,212 --> 00:08:39,482
(Final Round 2 begins.)

156
00:08:51,527 --> 00:08:53,465
I'm so curious
about what everyone is making.

157
00:08:53,729 --> 00:08:55,298
Can't we go and watch?

158
00:08:57,133 --> 00:08:59,435
- I'm dying to know.
- I really want to see.

159
00:08:59,435 --> 00:09:00,536
(What will their final pastries be?)

160
00:09:00,536 --> 00:09:02,371
I'm the one getting nervous today.

161
00:09:03,506 --> 00:09:05,640
It's going to be so high-pressure
because...

162
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:07,446
- so many masters are here.
- My hands are sweating.

163
00:09:07,447 --> 00:09:09,270
(Three Special Masters for the final)

164
00:09:11,347 --> 00:09:13,983
The atmosphere is so quiet.

165
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:15,785
It feels like I shouldn't even speak.

166
00:09:15,785 --> 00:09:17,753
(The factory is thick with tension
for the final.)

167
00:09:17,987 --> 00:09:19,488
I wonder what they're all making.

168
00:09:20,423 --> 00:09:22,658
There are so many Masters today.

169
00:09:22,658 --> 00:09:24,393
- Exactly.
- But the score difference...

170
00:09:24,393 --> 00:09:25,528
(8 Masters in total)

171
00:09:25,528 --> 00:09:27,330
(Higher scoring weight for the final)

172
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:31,367
- Even if you were last in Round One...
- You truly never know.

173
00:09:31,367 --> 00:09:32,501
With about 50 points...

174
00:09:32,526 --> 00:09:33,524
(A gap that can be completely overcome)

175
00:09:33,568 --> 00:09:35,504
- That's true.
- It's totally possible.

176
00:09:36,439 --> 00:09:39,311
Right now, the top three
need to play it safe,

177
00:09:40,544 --> 00:09:43,613
while 4th through 7th
should take big risks...

178
00:09:43,613 --> 00:09:44,683
and really go for it.

179
00:09:45,782 --> 00:09:49,952
Since they've made it this far,
their skills are likely on par.

180
00:09:49,952 --> 00:09:51,687
The key now is
who avoids making a mistake.

181
00:09:52,224 --> 00:09:56,454
In the end, it'll come down
to the level of perfection.

182
00:09:56,479 --> 00:09:58,793
(Final Round 2: A winner decided
by the narrowest of margins)

183
00:09:58,794 --> 00:10:01,230
Si Yeop looks so relaxed.

184
00:10:03,399 --> 00:10:06,702
Honestly, at this point,

185
00:10:06,714 --> 00:10:09,274
wouldn't it be worth aiming for the win?

186
00:10:10,488 --> 00:10:13,279
Since I've made it this far,
if I'm going to do it,

187
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:16,680
I feel like I have to win.

188
00:10:20,892 --> 00:10:22,153
Aren't those ginkgo nuts?

189
00:10:23,279 --> 00:10:24,615
- I think they're peanuts.
- Peanuts?

190
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:25,315
Yes.

191
00:10:25,757 --> 00:10:27,559
Since he's from Jeju Island,

192
00:10:28,322 --> 00:10:30,428
- I think they're Udo peanuts.
- Udo peanuts.

193
00:10:31,042 --> 00:10:33,129
Jeju Island is famous for its peanuts.

194
00:10:33,153 --> 00:10:35,100
That must be why he's using them.

195
00:10:37,408 --> 00:10:39,559
(Caramelized sugar...)

196
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:42,641
(over the Udo peanuts)

197
00:10:42,806 --> 00:10:44,364
My key point is...

198
00:10:44,388 --> 00:10:46,211
the Udo peanut praline.

199
00:10:47,206 --> 00:10:49,838
Since I'm someone who truly loves Udo...

200
00:10:50,349 --> 00:10:51,173
(Praline)

201
00:10:51,197 --> 00:10:53,036
(A traditional French confection made
by coating nuts like almonds...)

202
00:10:53,060 --> 00:10:54,086
(or hazelnuts in caramelized sugar)

203
00:10:56,857 --> 00:11:02,461
Because Si Yeop lives in Jeju Island,

204
00:11:02,903 --> 00:11:06,398
he definitely seems to use
a lot of Jeju ingredients.

205
00:11:11,782 --> 00:11:12,805
Alright.

206
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:16,975
(Finely ground Udo peanut praline)

207
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,040
Just one bite.

208
00:11:18,041 --> 00:11:19,945
(A visual that makes you want
just one bite)

209
00:11:20,193 --> 00:11:21,170
All right.

210
00:11:21,635 --> 00:11:22,502
That looks neat.

211
00:11:22,526 --> 00:11:23,697
Seamless.

212
00:11:24,270 --> 00:11:25,270
Next,

213
00:11:26,270 --> 00:11:29,788
I'm making pistachio praline the same way.

214
00:11:34,988 --> 00:11:36,616
I made pistachio whipped cream...

215
00:11:37,360 --> 00:11:39,067
and Udo peanut whipped cream.

216
00:11:39,920 --> 00:11:41,041
A lot is going on.

217
00:11:46,526 --> 00:11:47,824
Is he making a pastry?

218
00:11:47,848 --> 00:11:48,674
It looks like it.

219
00:11:49,606 --> 00:11:51,606
- It's his signature, so he has to use it.
- Exactly.

220
00:11:51,631 --> 00:11:53,077
(Si Yeop's signature: pastry)

221
00:11:55,632 --> 00:11:58,450
The first thing that came to mind was
that I had to do a pastry.

222
00:11:59,791 --> 00:12:02,554
I think Si Yeop is definitely
good at pastries.

223
00:12:02,554 --> 00:12:03,989
- This guy?
- Yes.

224
00:12:04,950 --> 00:12:07,025
You have to do what you're best at.

225
00:12:10,176 --> 00:12:12,531
(Placing the thinly rolled dough)

226
00:12:14,081 --> 00:12:14,941
(Cutting it against something?)

227
00:12:14,966 --> 00:12:15,589
What is that?

228
00:12:15,613 --> 00:12:17,426
- What kind of shape is that?
- What is that shape?

229
00:12:22,054 --> 00:12:23,997
What is he trying to make?

230
00:12:24,021 --> 00:12:26,245
It's my first time seeing a cut like this.

231
00:12:26,419 --> 00:12:27,446
What could it be?

232
00:12:31,725 --> 00:12:33,318
Peanuts and pistachios together?

233
00:12:33,525 --> 00:12:37,355
(Two types of cream, peanut and pistachio,
on the mysterious shape)

234
00:12:37,381 --> 00:12:39,231
That is very interesting, actually.

235
00:12:39,711 --> 00:12:42,457
Pistachios on one side,
peanuts on the other.

236
00:12:42,883 --> 00:12:44,391
And the shape is quite impressive.

237
00:12:44,391 --> 00:12:46,064
Maybe a butterfly or something.

238
00:12:46,331 --> 00:12:47,032
Could be.

239
00:12:51,709 --> 00:12:54,701
(The identity of the pastry is slowly
revealed as the edges are folded.)

240
00:12:54,702 --> 00:12:58,977
The shape is impressive
now that it's folded.

241
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:02,313
- Into a water drop shape.
- A water drop shape.

242
00:13:03,180 --> 00:13:05,059
It's really clever of him
to think of that.

243
00:13:05,406 --> 00:13:08,531
When he first cut it, I didn't know
it would turn out like a drop.

244
00:13:08,555 --> 00:13:10,339
He really thought it through.

245
00:13:12,492 --> 00:13:17,135
(Si Yeop's Ultimate Pastry
with water drop accents)

246
00:13:18,115 --> 00:13:22,367
(What kind of story will be contained
in Si Yeop's pastry?)

247
00:13:23,327 --> 00:13:26,091
(Meanwhile, another contestant
making a pastry)

248
00:13:27,007 --> 00:13:29,973
(Final Round 1, 2nd place: Gyeong Mu)

249
00:13:30,172 --> 00:13:33,678
It's a pastry battle between Si Yeop
and Gyeong Mu right now.

250
00:13:33,709 --> 00:13:34,502
Yes.

251
00:13:35,142 --> 00:13:37,485
It's the same pastry,

252
00:13:37,509 --> 00:13:40,219
but technically, it's about how well
they catch the fermentation point.

253
00:13:41,608 --> 00:13:43,901
Hasn't Gyeong Mu always been
in the top tier?

254
00:13:43,925 --> 00:13:44,911
- Yes.
- Consistently.

255
00:13:44,935 --> 00:13:46,825
Since he was in second place
twice in a row,

256
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:48,660
he needs to reclaim first place now.

257
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:53,145
The second-place team is
Team A Hungover Day.

258
00:13:53,170 --> 00:13:56,334
(2nd place in Round 2
"Perfect Day for Baked Goods")

259
00:13:56,635 --> 00:14:01,807
(2nd place in Round 4 "Local Heritage")

260
00:14:01,873 --> 00:14:06,177
(2nd place in Final Round 1
"Baked Goods for a Meal")

261
00:14:06,381 --> 00:14:08,301
He also took second place
at the international competition,

262
00:14:08,325 --> 00:14:09,556
"Coupe du Monde," right?

263
00:14:09,581 --> 00:14:10,611
(An inescapable cycle)

264
00:14:10,635 --> 00:14:12,984
He took second place
at the world competition too.

265
00:14:13,286 --> 00:14:14,708
You'll really need
to get first place this time.

266
00:14:14,732 --> 00:14:16,224
It would be such a shame
if he got second again.

267
00:14:16,248 --> 00:14:17,255
That can't happen.

268
00:14:17,705 --> 00:14:20,525
In the final, I absolutely have to take
first place once.

269
00:14:21,525 --> 00:14:24,229
I think it's time to be ambitious,

270
00:14:25,351 --> 00:14:29,334
and I feel like I need to burn bright
and take first place no matter what.

271
00:14:32,150 --> 00:14:34,105
Gyeong Mu brought beans.

272
00:14:34,764 --> 00:14:36,208
Cranberry beans.

273
00:14:36,234 --> 00:14:37,519
(Cranberry beans)

274
00:14:37,544 --> 00:14:39,178
He used those last time too.

275
00:14:39,426 --> 00:14:40,833
In A Twist on the Classics.

276
00:14:40,834 --> 00:14:43,548
(The ingredient used to defeat Sang Min
in Round 3, "A Twist on the Classics")

277
00:14:44,132 --> 00:14:47,586
Red bean pastry was the subject
I prepared.

278
00:14:48,605 --> 00:14:51,890
I thought the most Korean thing
would be the most global.

279
00:14:52,105 --> 00:14:56,017
That's also what we can show best.

280
00:14:56,950 --> 00:14:58,523
(The main ingredient boiled
in two separate batches)

281
00:14:58,524 --> 00:15:01,099
They are beans
with two different textures.

282
00:15:01,876 --> 00:15:04,569
I boil them according to the texture.

283
00:15:06,736 --> 00:15:09,174
I smell red beans boiling. Beans too.

284
00:15:15,994 --> 00:15:18,053
(First, the boiled cranberry beans)

285
00:15:18,054 --> 00:15:20,752
- Right now, Gyeong Mu...
- He's straining something.

286
00:15:21,649 --> 00:15:24,215
He's boiling them to make paste
and then straining them through a sieve.

287
00:15:24,239 --> 00:15:25,490
I think so too.

288
00:15:26,016 --> 00:15:29,060
Preparation is allowed, so I wonder
why he didn't make the paste in advance.

289
00:15:30,422 --> 00:15:33,807
(Gyeong Mu did not prepare
the time-consuming paste beforehand.)

290
00:15:33,832 --> 00:15:34,968
I think he was ambitious...

291
00:15:34,993 --> 00:15:37,335
and wanted to show the whole process
during the competition.

292
00:15:39,253 --> 00:15:42,407
I believe that showing as much
of what I can do as possible...

293
00:15:43,019 --> 00:15:45,310
is also an important part
of the competition.

294
00:15:46,712 --> 00:15:49,347
That's why I wanted to minimize
pre-competition preparation.

295
00:15:50,398 --> 00:15:53,311
(After mixing brown sugar
with the boiled red beans,)

296
00:15:54,511 --> 00:15:59,124
(Gyeong Mu begins mashing them by hand.)

297
00:16:04,016 --> 00:16:06,549
The red beans don't look fully boiled yet.

298
00:16:06,989 --> 00:16:09,757
I think they need more time.

299
00:16:09,781 --> 00:16:10,736
They look dry.

300
00:16:13,052 --> 00:16:14,739
Red bean rice cake? Omegi-tteok?

301
00:16:14,739 --> 00:16:16,841
- It feels like omegi-tteok, right?
- Yeah.

302
00:16:17,210 --> 00:16:19,623
Like the red bean filling in omegi-tteok,

303
00:16:20,336 --> 00:16:23,915
the point was to keep the natural flavor
of the red beans intact.

304
00:16:24,863 --> 00:16:26,184
That was the most important part.

305
00:16:26,697 --> 00:16:30,489
I'm really curious.
How will he create a new pastry...

306
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:34,522
using red bean, a common ingredient
in Korea and Asia.

307
00:16:37,317 --> 00:16:40,237
(Gyeong Mu finally begins shaping.)

308
00:16:40,238 --> 00:16:43,035
Gyeong Mu is making the dough.

309
00:16:45,382 --> 00:16:48,435
I made a cream using beans...

310
00:16:48,459 --> 00:16:50,168
that has a certain texture and sweetness.

311
00:16:50,169 --> 00:16:52,945
(Soy milk cream)

312
00:16:54,047 --> 00:16:57,437
(Clumping the red bean paste...)

313
00:16:57,461 --> 00:17:00,284
(and placing it on top of the cream)

314
00:17:00,519 --> 00:17:03,321
Gyeong Mu is putting the cream
and red beans together.

315
00:17:03,808 --> 00:17:04,956
Okay.

316
00:17:06,752 --> 00:17:08,226
That looks delicious.

317
00:17:09,227 --> 00:17:10,895
It might go really well with the cream.

318
00:17:12,731 --> 00:17:14,666
He's making them
like he's folding dumplings.

319
00:17:14,667 --> 00:17:17,736
(Carefully shaping the pastry,
as if handling a baby)

320
00:17:18,102 --> 00:17:20,293
He only looks like a macho man.

321
00:17:20,317 --> 00:17:21,740
- He's actually very delicate.
- So delicate.

322
00:17:22,062 --> 00:17:23,375
Master Kim is like that too.

323
00:17:25,796 --> 00:17:27,112
Even though you look like a boss.

324
00:17:28,346 --> 00:17:30,661
(Placing the dough
into taegeuk-shaped molds to ferment)

325
00:17:30,662 --> 00:17:32,116
He's capturing the taegeuk shape.

326
00:17:32,140 --> 00:17:34,252
I wanted to instill the pride...

327
00:17:34,994 --> 00:17:37,823
of the South Korean flag.

328
00:17:38,526 --> 00:17:41,526
The passion I feel
when I see the taegeuk pattern.

329
00:17:42,106 --> 00:17:44,396
When considering it
as a commercial product,

330
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:50,684
I also liked the idea of comparing
and eating two different pastries.

331
00:17:51,164 --> 00:17:53,004
The top and bottom must have
different flavors.

332
00:17:53,344 --> 00:17:55,243
That's why he boiled two types of paste.

333
00:17:56,670 --> 00:18:01,246
(The other taegeuk pastry contains
cranberry bean paste.)

334
00:18:02,006 --> 00:18:06,065
I added the sweetness
and tanginess of Hallabong.

335
00:18:06,878 --> 00:18:09,162
So basically, he's producing
two different flavors?

336
00:18:09,187 --> 00:18:09,883
- Yes.
- Yes.

337
00:18:09,914 --> 00:18:11,765
- Because of the South Korean flag.
- The flag pattern.

338
00:18:11,869 --> 00:18:12,991
That's good.

339
00:18:13,518 --> 00:18:16,449
Gyeong Mu is really...

340
00:18:16,473 --> 00:18:18,763
going all-in on the Korean theme.

341
00:18:20,632 --> 00:18:22,834
Since it's the final,
it seems they are using...

342
00:18:22,859 --> 00:18:26,089
their signature ingredients
that they're best at.

343
00:18:26,723 --> 00:18:30,281
In the final, I think it's good
to let go of a bit of greed.

344
00:18:30,282 --> 00:18:33,301
Rather than trying to show too much,
do what you're good at,

345
00:18:34,254 --> 00:18:35,414
the thing you can do
with your eyes closed.

346
00:18:35,415 --> 00:18:37,182
(Advice from a competition veteran)

347
00:18:38,613 --> 00:18:41,519
(What Ultimate Pastry has
Hwa Young prepared?)

348
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:44,322
I'm curious
about Hwa Young's creation too.

349
00:18:46,865 --> 00:18:48,326
What is he taking out?

350
00:18:50,564 --> 00:18:52,230
It's a hard-style dough.

351
00:18:52,363 --> 00:18:54,399
He even brought bamboo baskets.

352
00:18:55,744 --> 00:18:58,036
- I think he's making sourdough.
- That sounds delicious.

353
00:18:58,384 --> 00:19:00,439
Didn't he make sourdough in Round One too?

354
00:19:00,610 --> 00:19:02,528
- The Reuben sandwich.
- The sandwich.

355
00:19:02,992 --> 00:19:04,182
That was truly delicious.

356
00:19:05,196 --> 00:19:10,398
(He was praised for his signature pastry,
the Reuben sandwich.)

357
00:19:10,399 --> 00:19:12,572
If someone who cooks is
also good at baking,

358
00:19:12,596 --> 00:19:14,653
what are we supposed to do for a living?

359
00:19:18,217 --> 00:19:20,292
It kind of reminds me of Round One.

360
00:19:20,293 --> 00:19:22,294
(Dough that looks similar
to the Reuben sandwich bread)

361
00:19:22,977 --> 00:19:25,641
It's a pastry that's supposed
to conquer the world...

362
00:19:26,088 --> 00:19:28,867
I wonder what kind of Korean element
he's going for.

363
00:19:29,286 --> 00:19:33,138
Maybe he's trying to adopt
the worldview he loves?

364
00:19:34,832 --> 00:19:37,175
The word "campagne" might be the same,

365
00:19:37,684 --> 00:19:39,377
but since this is a genre,

366
00:19:39,401 --> 00:19:42,347
you should consider it
a completely separate food.

367
00:19:42,570 --> 00:19:45,582
I worry about how the older generation
in Korea...

368
00:19:45,583 --> 00:19:48,720
can enjoy healthy baked goods
even more deliciously.

369
00:19:49,116 --> 00:19:52,924
I worked hard to look after health
while capturing the flavor.

370
00:19:54,535 --> 00:19:56,816
By eating my pastry,

371
00:19:56,840 --> 00:20:00,098
I want to suggest good ways...

372
00:20:00,123 --> 00:20:02,859
for people to lead a healthy life.

373
00:20:02,859 --> 00:20:05,792
(A bread that captures his long-standing
contemplations as a baker)

374
00:20:06,459 --> 00:20:09,326
I think he's the only one
who's making bread.

375
00:20:09,326 --> 00:20:11,959
- His specialty is sourdough.
- Sourdough? Okay.

376
00:20:12,226 --> 00:20:14,492
Well, that's kind of a soft spot for me.

377
00:20:14,492 --> 00:20:16,859
- Because I really miss bread.
- Oh, really?

378
00:20:16,859 --> 00:20:20,626
Because in Korea, it's easy to find
high-quality breads,

379
00:20:20,626 --> 00:20:25,292
but a good loaf of everyday bread is
not easy to find.

380
00:20:25,292 --> 00:20:28,826
- It's usually the soft ones, right?
- Yes.

381
00:20:29,959 --> 00:20:31,292
Is that cheese inside?

382
00:20:31,292 --> 00:20:33,592
Cheese and... Is that black sesame?

383
00:20:33,592 --> 00:20:34,926
(What are those black grains
in the dough?)

384
00:20:34,926 --> 00:20:37,326
I wanted to add a Korean touch,

385
00:20:37,326 --> 00:20:38,526
so I added perilla seeds.

386
00:20:38,526 --> 00:20:42,726
Because the health benefits
of perilla seeds...

387
00:20:42,726 --> 00:20:44,826
have been in the spotlight lately.

388
00:20:45,226 --> 00:20:48,892
It's hard to balance the fats
when it comes to the nutrients in bread,

389
00:20:51,626 --> 00:20:54,359
and perilla seeds
can supplement that perfectly.

390
00:20:54,692 --> 00:20:59,226
And cheese is
another great source of protein.

391
00:20:59,826 --> 00:21:03,759
It's a mix of sour, sweet,
and salty flavors.

392
00:21:03,759 --> 00:21:06,059
So it's a bread that truly satisfies
the palate...

393
00:21:06,059 --> 00:21:08,526
even without spreading anything on it.

394
00:21:08,526 --> 00:21:12,459
(A bread that's delicious all on its own)

395
00:21:14,459 --> 00:21:16,826
Is he baking the bread already?

396
00:21:17,292 --> 00:21:19,092
Please come out well.

397
00:21:20,226 --> 00:21:23,559
(Hwa Young aims to win with nothing
but a single loaf of bread.)

398
00:21:25,092 --> 00:21:29,726
(Will his bread turn out right?)

399
00:21:32,626 --> 00:21:34,326
- I think it's already done.
- The bread is coming out.

400
00:21:34,326 --> 00:21:35,259
Here it comes.

401
00:21:39,259 --> 00:21:41,292
- The bread looks great.
- Yes.

402
00:21:41,292 --> 00:21:42,659
The bread turned out beautifully.

403
00:21:45,192 --> 00:21:46,826
It looks delicious.

404
00:21:46,826 --> 00:21:49,192
I'd love to try just one slice
of that sourdough.

405
00:21:50,726 --> 00:21:53,992
It's the bread I'm most confident in
out of everything I've ever made.

406
00:21:54,492 --> 00:21:56,026
Just looking at it, I could tell,
"This must be good."

407
00:21:57,259 --> 00:21:59,326
Everything turned out really well overall.

408
00:21:59,326 --> 00:22:00,692
(Golden-brown sourdough)

409
00:22:01,292 --> 00:22:04,059
But that can't be enough for him
to win today.

410
00:22:04,059 --> 00:22:07,026
He definitely won't stop at just that.

411
00:22:07,026 --> 00:22:08,959
He has his own specialty, after all.

412
00:22:08,959 --> 00:22:11,659
I think he'll add something else
that pairs well with it.

413
00:22:11,659 --> 00:22:16,092
(What is Hwa Young's secret addition
to the bread?)

414
00:22:17,159 --> 00:22:19,392
I'm also curious
about what Jin Seo will do.

415
00:22:19,826 --> 00:22:23,759
Will he show us something dainty
and cute again today?

416
00:22:24,326 --> 00:22:26,226
For the Final Round Two...

417
00:22:27,026 --> 00:22:30,059
I'm going to do
what I love and what I'm best at.

418
00:22:37,392 --> 00:22:39,659
- What's that?
- Sugar craft?

419
00:22:39,926 --> 00:22:41,926
(He brought out the lamp for sugar work.)

420
00:22:42,626 --> 00:22:44,759
(Overwhelmed)

421
00:22:46,292 --> 00:22:49,243
Challenger Kim Jin Seo is doing
sugar work?

422
00:22:49,244 --> 00:22:50,492
- Today?
- Really?

423
00:22:51,559 --> 00:22:53,426
- Isn't this the first time?
- Yes, the very first time.

424
00:22:53,426 --> 00:22:57,059
(The Masters are also focused on him.)

425
00:23:00,226 --> 00:23:01,759
Since I've made it to the finals,

426
00:23:01,759 --> 00:23:05,826
I feel like I want to prove myself.

427
00:23:07,359 --> 00:23:10,226
Anyway, the final theme is
"Ultimate Pastry."

428
00:23:10,226 --> 00:23:11,759
And it's the finale.

429
00:23:11,759 --> 00:23:13,759
- Storytelling will be key.
- Exactly.

430
00:23:13,759 --> 00:23:17,026
Your own personal story.

431
00:23:17,026 --> 00:23:18,592
Though taste is important too, of course.

432
00:23:18,592 --> 00:23:20,692
(What is the story
behind Jin Seo's bread?)

433
00:23:21,192 --> 00:23:24,226
The Ultimate Pastry I'll be presenting
for this mission is...

434
00:23:24,559 --> 00:23:27,159
"The Gold Medal of My Life."

435
00:23:27,792 --> 00:23:30,259
I expressed the medal
with a mousse cake...

436
00:23:30,259 --> 00:23:33,259
and the ribbon through sugar work.

437
00:23:35,559 --> 00:23:37,392
When I won the silver medal
in the pastry category...

438
00:23:37,392 --> 00:23:38,892
at the National Skills Competition,

439
00:23:38,892 --> 00:23:41,078
that was the first time
I encountered sugar work.

440
00:23:42,259 --> 00:23:45,192
It's what I love most
and feel most confident in,

441
00:23:45,192 --> 00:23:47,526
but I haven't shown it on this show yet.

442
00:23:47,526 --> 00:23:50,826
So I wanted to showcase it
this time as an extra.

443
00:23:52,359 --> 00:23:55,359
Jin Seo is showing us something
he's kept hidden until now.

444
00:23:55,359 --> 00:23:57,359
(Jin Seo aims to raise
with his hidden technique.)

445
00:24:00,192 --> 00:24:01,598
I would never do that.

446
00:24:01,599 --> 00:24:03,798
I would never do that in a competition...

447
00:24:03,799 --> 00:24:07,392
unless it were
a specific sugar work challenge.

448
00:24:08,559 --> 00:24:10,721
This is very ambitious. Yes.

449
00:24:10,722 --> 00:24:12,226
Very ambitious.

450
00:24:12,359 --> 00:24:14,541
I think he wants to make up
for his sixth-place finish.

451
00:24:15,026 --> 00:24:19,459
But that could either be
a hindrance or a help.

452
00:24:19,459 --> 00:24:22,426
Still, he should do everything he wants
for the last time.

453
00:24:26,392 --> 00:24:30,459
(What results will the sugar work
bring for Jin Seo?)

454
00:24:31,792 --> 00:24:34,759
In fact, sugar craft can be
a double-edged sword.

455
00:24:34,759 --> 00:24:37,559
But the reason I decided to try it was...

456
00:24:38,126 --> 00:24:42,326
that I was so confident and certain.

457
00:24:46,059 --> 00:24:49,026
You need good hand and arm strength
for sugar work.

458
00:24:49,026 --> 00:24:49,859
Grip strength?

459
00:24:50,992 --> 00:24:53,026
- You need power when you're pulling it.
- Muscle strength.

460
00:24:58,092 --> 00:25:00,759
What is he trying to make right now?

461
00:25:01,392 --> 00:25:02,226
What is that?

462
00:25:02,792 --> 00:25:03,959
What is that shape?

463
00:25:06,992 --> 00:25:09,659
(Is that the French flag?)

464
00:25:09,659 --> 00:25:10,859
Is this France?

465
00:25:13,293 --> 00:25:15,281
(He is French.)

466
00:25:16,626 --> 00:25:17,892
(Preparing to pull the sugar)

467
00:25:17,892 --> 00:25:20,192
Jin Seo works really hard
on the technical side.

468
00:25:21,159 --> 00:25:24,692
- Truly. I'm genuinely rooting for him.
- Me too.

469
00:25:24,692 --> 00:25:25,792
But what is that, really?

470
00:25:35,826 --> 00:25:37,326
- That looks cool!
- Hey!

471
00:25:37,726 --> 00:25:38,959
It's beautiful.

472
00:25:40,826 --> 00:25:41,792
Go, go.

473
00:25:42,359 --> 00:25:45,226
- Let's go, you can do it!
- You're so cool!

474
00:25:54,526 --> 00:25:57,392
There are many people
who can do sugar ribbons.

475
00:25:57,959 --> 00:26:00,992
But it's difficult to make them
as long as I do.

476
00:26:03,326 --> 00:26:04,259
He got it.

477
00:26:04,259 --> 00:26:06,592
- It's so long.
- It's a total eye-catcher.

478
00:26:07,392 --> 00:26:08,492
- He's better.
- Yeah.

479
00:26:08,492 --> 00:26:09,926
Nice.

480
00:26:11,359 --> 00:26:12,392
Truly fantastic.

481
00:26:13,059 --> 00:26:14,398
He even looks sexy doing it.

482
00:26:15,859 --> 00:26:19,326
Right. It's the final competition,
and he has to do what he's best at.

483
00:26:20,492 --> 00:26:23,392
(Jin Seo pulled the ribbon-shaped
sugar dough over 2 meters long.)

484
00:26:25,859 --> 00:26:26,692
That's impressive.

485
00:26:27,592 --> 00:26:30,492
Jin Seo is bending the sugar work now.

486
00:26:30,892 --> 00:26:33,059
- To shape it into a medal necklace.
- Right!

487
00:26:33,059 --> 00:26:34,192
Even that!

488
00:26:34,192 --> 00:26:35,159
It's really beautiful.

489
00:26:35,659 --> 00:26:36,792
That actually looks like a ribbon.

490
00:26:39,259 --> 00:26:42,559
He showed every single skill he has.

491
00:26:44,492 --> 00:26:45,692
He's in his prime.

492
00:26:47,826 --> 00:26:51,459
(Hwang Ji Oh, 4th place in Final Round 1)

493
00:26:51,926 --> 00:26:53,203
I have to turn the tables.

494
00:26:53,859 --> 00:26:56,926
I've prepared very hard for that.

495
00:26:57,592 --> 00:26:58,859
I came in fourth...

496
00:26:58,859 --> 00:27:00,592
(Ji Oh dropped from 1st to 4th place.)

497
00:27:00,859 --> 00:27:02,679
I couldn't just sit still.

498
00:27:03,759 --> 00:27:06,426
(The Hwangs' Chicken Bread
presented in Final Round 1)

499
00:27:07,126 --> 00:27:07,992
I got a bit greedy.

500
00:27:07,992 --> 00:27:10,126
- Hurry.
- Only one minute left?

501
00:27:11,892 --> 00:27:16,359
(Evaluated as lacking completion
due to a failure in time management)

502
00:27:16,559 --> 00:27:20,426
The 4th place is Crazy Patissiere,
Hwang Ji Oh.

503
00:27:20,859 --> 00:27:22,226
(Became 4th place
with a 24-point gap from 1st place)

504
00:27:22,226 --> 00:27:26,059
With that kind of score difference,
couldn't it be overturned?

505
00:27:26,959 --> 00:27:28,326
The thing I can do best.

506
00:27:28,726 --> 00:27:30,059
Everything I have.

507
00:27:30,492 --> 00:27:32,959
Even things that go beyond my limits.

508
00:27:32,959 --> 00:27:35,292
I thought I had to pull out everything.

509
00:27:36,226 --> 00:27:37,792
Let's start with me.

510
00:27:38,726 --> 00:27:42,159
(What is the main ingredient Ji Oh chose?)

511
00:27:42,759 --> 00:27:43,887
It's persimmon.

512
00:27:43,888 --> 00:27:45,459
(Diced braised sweet persimmon)

513
00:27:47,859 --> 00:27:50,292
Persimmon, the first dessert of my life,

514
00:27:50,292 --> 00:27:56,359
I wanted to make it using
every possible skill and all my sincerity.

515
00:27:56,826 --> 00:27:59,226
As a dessert,

516
00:27:59,226 --> 00:28:00,792
Persimmon isn't particularly impactful.

517
00:28:02,226 --> 00:28:04,892
I've got and tasted
every kind of persimmon.

518
00:28:07,226 --> 00:28:10,192
There is also soft Daebong too.

519
00:28:10,192 --> 00:28:12,992
I've tried turning sweet persimmons
into soft ones.

520
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:14,626
I've also tried just eating
sweet persimmons.

521
00:28:14,626 --> 00:28:17,054
Dried persimmons with a chewy texture,

522
00:28:17,055 --> 00:28:19,092
and even well-dried, firm ones...

523
00:28:19,092 --> 00:28:21,892
I've tasted many types of persimmons.

524
00:28:21,892 --> 00:28:24,439
I thought a lot about
which taste and aroma...

525
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,859
of the persimmon to highlight.

526
00:28:27,192 --> 00:28:29,292
(Coming after endless testing
and long contemplation...)

527
00:28:29,659 --> 00:28:30,834
It's a soft persimmon.

528
00:28:30,835 --> 00:28:31,826
(Soft persimmon sauce)

529
00:28:31,826 --> 00:28:33,103
Did she mix gelatin in there?

530
00:28:33,104 --> 00:28:35,305
I think she made it into a jelly
and then blended it.

531
00:28:35,859 --> 00:28:37,492
Oh, there are dried persimmons too.

532
00:28:37,492 --> 00:28:40,226
The ingredients are all persimmon-based.

533
00:28:40,792 --> 00:28:42,992
It's a cake permeated with persimmons.

534
00:28:45,926 --> 00:28:46,892
I like her idea.

535
00:28:48,026 --> 00:28:49,226
You're wonderful, Ji Oh!

536
00:28:54,292 --> 00:28:57,226
(Putting compote into a half-sphere mold
lined with plastic wrap)

537
00:28:57,226 --> 00:28:59,592
- She'll probably freeze or set it.
- Looks like it.

538
00:28:59,592 --> 00:29:01,359
Since she's using plastic wrap.

539
00:29:02,592 --> 00:29:06,859
(Wrapping it into a ball shape
with the plastic wrap)

540
00:29:08,492 --> 00:29:13,192
(First step completed
by putting it into the blast freezer)

541
00:29:15,592 --> 00:29:21,226
I was more nervous,
and I prepared more thoroughly.

542
00:29:21,226 --> 00:29:24,292
I didn't want to waste a single second.

543
00:29:24,292 --> 00:29:25,559
That's how I moved.

544
00:29:31,026 --> 00:29:33,326
(On the other hand)

545
00:29:34,526 --> 00:29:37,492
Min Su looks very relaxed today.

546
00:29:38,026 --> 00:29:40,092
Actually, since he's in 7th place,

547
00:29:40,092 --> 00:29:41,726
he might feel less nervous.

548
00:29:42,459 --> 00:29:45,826
Sometimes you get better results
when you let go.

549
00:29:46,959 --> 00:29:48,559
He seems somewhat stable.

550
00:29:53,726 --> 00:29:56,192
My mind was more at ease.
I felt lighthearted...

551
00:29:56,692 --> 00:29:58,459
Looking back,

552
00:29:58,459 --> 00:30:02,559
this competition turned me into a monster.

553
00:30:02,758 --> 00:30:04,660
(Round Two, Pop-up Team Mission)

554
00:30:05,462 --> 00:30:08,535
I think I got caught up,
without even realizing,

555
00:30:08,536 --> 00:30:11,268
in the obsession of doing
something different.

556
00:30:12,901 --> 00:30:14,670
(Round Four, Local Heritage)

557
00:30:14,853 --> 00:30:17,904
I felt like being trapped in that mindset
only made me more prone to mistakes.

558
00:30:18,474 --> 00:30:21,944
In the end,
I decided to stick to what I always do...

559
00:30:21,944 --> 00:30:24,914
no matter what others were doing.

560
00:30:24,915 --> 00:30:27,916
I was confident with that in mind.

561
00:30:28,683 --> 00:30:32,022
(What is Min Su's Ultimate Pastry?)

562
00:30:32,654 --> 00:30:34,122
- Sweet potato?
- Roasted sweet potato!

563
00:30:34,389 --> 00:30:35,757
Is it a honey sweet potato?

564
00:30:36,258 --> 00:30:37,459
- Sweet potato!
- Sweet potato.

565
00:30:40,796 --> 00:30:42,030
I can smell it from here.

566
00:30:42,431 --> 00:30:43,799
- Fantastic.
- Yes.

567
00:30:44,334 --> 00:30:46,435
The oldest street food in Korea.

568
00:30:46,702 --> 00:30:50,005
It just reminds me of the time
walking through the street...

569
00:30:50,005 --> 00:30:52,941
and when you find a place selling that,

570
00:30:52,941 --> 00:30:55,344
you just can't help it once you smell it.

571
00:30:55,344 --> 00:30:57,346
You can't stop yourself.
You have to go and get one.

572
00:30:59,148 --> 00:31:01,950
Anything with sweet potato is
usually delicious.

573
00:31:01,950 --> 00:31:02,951
That's true.

574
00:31:04,626 --> 00:31:06,523
What is he trying to do with that?

575
00:31:06,955 --> 00:31:08,592
I think he's making a sweet potato cake.

576
00:31:09,124 --> 00:31:10,326
- With that...
- How?

577
00:31:10,326 --> 00:31:11,894
He's using it for the base.

578
00:31:21,203 --> 00:31:24,106
(15 minutes later)

579
00:31:26,041 --> 00:31:27,676
Min Su's is out.

580
00:31:27,676 --> 00:31:29,513
The one he put in the oven earlier.

581
00:31:30,512 --> 00:31:32,381
It's a beautiful golden brown.

582
00:31:32,481 --> 00:31:33,616
It looks delicious.

583
00:31:33,949 --> 00:31:34,950
(Oh)

584
00:31:41,323 --> 00:31:42,624
The smell is incredible.

585
00:31:43,126 --> 00:31:45,994
- I want to go down there and smell it.
- Yes.

586
00:31:46,395 --> 00:31:49,164
And I think we can partially feel it.

587
00:31:50,266 --> 00:31:55,037
My Ultimate Pastry is
a dessert called "Mountain."

588
00:31:55,537 --> 00:31:57,172
It's inspired by the Mont Blanc.

589
00:31:57,541 --> 00:31:59,408
Using that as my motif,

590
00:31:59,742 --> 00:32:02,277
I'm recreating it...

591
00:32:02,878 --> 00:32:04,446
using Korean ingredients.

592
00:32:07,683 --> 00:32:10,419
Min Su is taking out the molds!

593
00:32:11,286 --> 00:32:12,387
They're shaped like mountains.

594
00:32:13,355 --> 00:32:14,823
What's going in there?

595
00:32:15,190 --> 00:32:18,393
I've visually captured the beauty
of a mountain in spring.

596
00:32:19,462 --> 00:32:20,697
I made a chantilly using Gamhongro,

597
00:32:20,698 --> 00:32:23,065
a famous traditional liquor
from the Joseon dynasty,

598
00:32:23,865 --> 00:32:26,101
and then a bokbunja gel.

599
00:32:26,802 --> 00:32:29,938
(Bokbunja gel)

600
00:32:30,539 --> 00:32:33,108
(Sweet potato cream)

601
00:32:33,108 --> 00:32:35,377
I also used sweet potato mousse...

602
00:32:35,544 --> 00:32:38,113
to add more depth to the flavor.

603
00:32:40,414 --> 00:32:43,263
(After cutting the cake sheet
with a circular mold,)

604
00:32:46,955 --> 00:32:48,657
He's putting the ingredients
into the mold.

605
00:32:50,093 --> 00:32:51,860
What I cared about the most was...

606
00:32:52,262 --> 00:32:54,331
the harmony of flavors,

607
00:32:54,332 --> 00:32:56,265
rather than showing off flashy techniques,

608
00:32:58,467 --> 00:33:01,303
and whether these various components
go well with the taste.

609
00:33:02,571 --> 00:33:04,706
That's what I focused on.

610
00:33:05,507 --> 00:33:07,542
He used to design such complex flavors.

611
00:33:08,143 --> 00:33:10,946
But I think he's taking
the simplest approach today.

612
00:33:16,185 --> 00:33:18,120
- What's that?
- It's so colorful.

613
00:33:18,826 --> 00:33:21,189
Are those flowers? Edible flowers?

614
00:33:21,390 --> 00:33:22,991
Edible flowers?

615
00:33:23,792 --> 00:33:26,562
Flowers can play a big role in baking.

616
00:33:26,562 --> 00:33:27,962
(Meringue)

617
00:33:29,365 --> 00:33:30,566
He's sprinkling the flowers.

618
00:33:30,833 --> 00:33:32,234
- That's lovely.
- The colors are beautiful.

619
00:33:32,234 --> 00:33:33,226
It is.

620
00:33:33,227 --> 00:33:35,037
(Like spring flowers fluttering
on a snow-covered street)

621
00:33:37,739 --> 00:33:42,010
(Putting the flower meringues
into the oven)

622
00:33:48,417 --> 00:33:52,721
(Next, he takes out the set molds
from the blast freezer.)

623
00:33:57,626 --> 00:33:58,760
It's really a mountain.

624
00:33:59,444 --> 00:34:00,696
The top and bottom are different.

625
00:34:00,862 --> 00:34:02,699
So this is like a Mont Blanc, right?

626
00:34:03,832 --> 00:34:05,969
Like a Mont Blanc with sweet potato,

627
00:34:05,970 --> 00:34:07,637
a little bit different,
not using chestnut,

628
00:34:07,638 --> 00:34:08,870
but using something else.

629
00:34:09,071 --> 00:34:12,174
You know, for Mont Blanc,
they used to use blackberry.

630
00:34:12,507 --> 00:34:15,944
But instead of blackberries,
he used bokbunja, the Korean berry.

631
00:34:15,944 --> 00:34:18,748
- Okay, that's fine.
- And the sweet potatoes...

632
00:34:19,448 --> 00:34:20,682
and meringue.

633
00:34:21,650 --> 00:34:24,654
- A new fashion of a Mont Blanc.
- Yes, the Korean version of it.

634
00:34:30,792 --> 00:34:33,862
(Walnut crumble)

635
00:34:40,569 --> 00:34:41,803
The colors are really pretty.

636
00:34:42,404 --> 00:34:43,940
- It's two-toned.
- Looks delicious.

637
00:34:45,207 --> 00:34:50,245
(Sweet potato mousse
embracing the mountain)

638
00:34:50,946 --> 00:34:52,080
That looks tasty.

639
00:34:54,883 --> 00:34:57,619
There's something
I often say to my customers.

640
00:34:58,053 --> 00:35:01,123
"I hope you have a sweet moment,
even if it's just for a while."

641
00:35:01,123 --> 00:35:02,457
I always say that.

642
00:35:03,726 --> 00:35:05,273
When you're exhausted from daily life,

643
00:35:05,274 --> 00:35:07,020
I hope this sweet dessert brings you...

644
00:35:08,430 --> 00:35:10,098
a moment of happiness.

645
00:35:11,267 --> 00:35:14,937
That is what I consider
an Ultimate Pastry.

646
00:35:16,071 --> 00:35:18,206
(How will Min Su's "Mountain" turn out?)

647
00:35:19,174 --> 00:35:23,512
(Jin Seo heading to the oven)

648
00:35:26,982 --> 00:35:31,320
(The cake sheet
that will be shaped into a medal)

649
00:35:32,287 --> 00:35:35,057
(He starts cutting the base.)

650
00:35:35,390 --> 00:35:37,459
Jin Seo's sheet is out already.

651
00:35:37,459 --> 00:35:38,727
That was fast.

652
00:35:39,161 --> 00:35:43,398
(After cutting it with a circular mold)

653
00:35:46,001 --> 00:35:50,772
(Separating the parchment paper
from the cake sheet)

654
00:35:52,408 --> 00:35:55,043
He's peeling the sheet off,
but it doesn't look right.

655
00:35:55,043 --> 00:35:58,180
(The parchment paper isn't
coming off easily.)

656
00:35:58,447 --> 00:36:01,545
(The sheet finally starts to crumble.)

657
00:36:01,883 --> 00:36:03,619
- Gosh.
- Oh my.

658
00:36:03,619 --> 00:36:05,921
The sheet is sticking to the paper
and tearing apart.

659
00:36:05,921 --> 00:36:07,456
It's like watching myself
in the last round.

660
00:36:08,156 --> 00:36:09,691
Things just aren't going his way.

661
00:36:09,691 --> 00:36:12,961
(A sense of foreboding)

662
00:36:18,834 --> 00:36:20,102
It's not coming off.

663
00:36:20,602 --> 00:36:21,469
That's...

664
00:36:24,277 --> 00:36:26,379
(Nearly half of the sheet
ends up damaged.)

665
00:36:27,342 --> 00:36:28,977
- It's because he's panicking.
- Right?

666
00:36:28,977 --> 00:36:30,078
(He's flustered.)

667
00:36:30,345 --> 00:36:31,251
It's chaotic now.

668
00:36:31,252 --> 00:36:33,181
He's in such a rush
that his hands are shaking...

669
00:36:34,016 --> 00:36:35,617
He probably can't see straight right now.

670
00:36:36,853 --> 00:36:40,555
I felt like things were going wrong
on purpose today.

671
00:36:40,789 --> 00:36:42,491
In all my time competing,

672
00:36:42,491 --> 00:36:44,927
I've never lost my cool like this.

673
00:36:45,160 --> 00:36:47,095
But today, I just did.

674
00:36:48,397 --> 00:36:50,332
That's what happens when you're nervous.

675
00:36:50,332 --> 00:36:53,702
- He's too nervous right now.
- You can miss the very basic,

676
00:36:53,702 --> 00:36:55,675
even routine things.

677
00:36:55,676 --> 00:36:57,339
Jin Seo's face has gone pale.

678
00:36:59,207 --> 00:37:00,542
He needs to stay calm.

679
00:37:03,111 --> 00:37:04,513
(Can he overcome this?)

680
00:37:04,513 --> 00:37:05,647
I really hope he pulls through.

681
00:37:07,483 --> 00:37:10,285
Yeong Seok's sheet is also out now.

682
00:37:11,620 --> 00:37:13,055
This one is baked perfectly.

683
00:37:14,690 --> 00:37:18,427
(Starting to cut calmly)

684
00:37:21,196 --> 00:37:22,764
(Fluffy and clean)

685
00:37:24,525 --> 00:37:26,302
Jin Seo should've been that composed.

686
00:37:28,337 --> 00:37:30,772
Exactly.
That's how a sheet is supposed to look.

687
00:37:31,906 --> 00:37:35,512
(Frantic vs. Calm)

688
00:37:36,078 --> 00:37:40,482
(The two sheets look quite different.)

689
00:37:40,916 --> 00:37:43,118
Yeong Seok is being so calm today.

690
00:37:46,688 --> 00:37:49,124
Yeong Seok has grown immensely too.

691
00:37:49,124 --> 00:37:52,893
He's been studying constantly
for the past three months.

692
00:37:52,894 --> 00:37:55,797
He's showing massive growth
with every passing episode.

693
00:37:58,133 --> 00:37:59,202
When I...

694
00:38:00,567 --> 00:38:03,473
first got into baking,
I didn't start with the basics.

695
00:38:03,474 --> 00:38:07,209
I went straight into the field
to work at a bakery.

696
00:38:08,510 --> 00:38:11,713
Back then, I just made bread
like a machine.

697
00:38:12,347 --> 00:38:14,149
But now, I'm actually having fun.

698
00:38:14,149 --> 00:38:15,250
(Rediscovering the joy of baking)

699
00:38:15,617 --> 00:38:17,319
I want to keep growing.

700
00:38:17,986 --> 00:38:19,699
Through this competition,

701
00:38:19,700 --> 00:38:22,491
I want to be recognized
as Ju Yeong Seok, the patissier.

702
00:38:23,559 --> 00:38:26,862
(What is the Ultimate Pastry
from the growth-hungry Yeong Seok?)

703
00:38:29,531 --> 00:38:31,500
(Black rice)

704
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:33,001
He's using black rice.

705
00:38:34,103 --> 00:38:36,204
- Is that very Korean?
- Yes.

706
00:38:36,204 --> 00:38:38,741
- It's used in Italy as well, right?
- Absolutely.

707
00:38:38,741 --> 00:38:40,543
We have black rice,

708
00:38:40,544 --> 00:38:43,011
but it's traditionally cooked
in a completely different way.

709
00:38:43,011 --> 00:38:44,179
(Black rice used in risotto and salads)

710
00:38:44,546 --> 00:38:48,481
Because black rice in a dessert
isn't something we use much...

711
00:38:48,482 --> 00:38:50,351
in French pastry, right? I mean...

712
00:38:50,352 --> 00:38:52,120
What is he trying to make with it?

713
00:38:55,057 --> 00:38:57,526
The highlight of my Ultimate Pastry is
the black rice.

714
00:38:59,795 --> 00:39:04,365
Since it'll provide a crunchy texture
and a nutty aroma,

715
00:39:04,365 --> 00:39:06,301
it's going to play
the most important role.

716
00:39:09,605 --> 00:39:12,674
(This time, he adds something
to the batter.)

717
00:39:13,775 --> 00:39:15,544
- It's black.
- Something black?

718
00:39:15,644 --> 00:39:17,747
I think he's adding squid ink.

719
00:39:20,983 --> 00:39:24,219
(Black batter added with squid ink)

720
00:39:30,125 --> 00:39:31,226
It's a crepe.

721
00:39:38,134 --> 00:39:40,402
And with the crepe,
I still cannot see where it's going.

722
00:39:40,469 --> 00:39:42,437
What's going to be the final look of it.

723
00:39:42,437 --> 00:39:44,539
I think he's trying to express
something in black.

724
00:39:44,539 --> 00:39:48,043
Looking at the concept,
he's got both black rice and squid ink.

725
00:39:48,310 --> 00:39:50,680
My life has been full of ups and downs.

726
00:39:50,681 --> 00:39:52,861
There were times
when things were extremely difficult,

727
00:39:52,886 --> 00:39:55,384
but there were good times as well.

728
00:39:55,818 --> 00:39:59,187
I'm using black to symbolize
those hardest times.

729
00:39:59,187 --> 00:40:00,456
(The inside is a contrasting white)

730
00:40:00,456 --> 00:40:04,928
Then I'm creating layers that
gradually turn white on the inside.

731
00:40:11,458 --> 00:40:14,078
Rather than being sweet,
I plan on making a cream...

732
00:40:14,258 --> 00:40:16,814
that's nutty and leaves
a lingering flavor.

733
00:40:19,309 --> 00:40:21,990
(Yeong Seok's signature cream)

734
00:40:21,991 --> 00:40:23,853
Yeong Seok has pulled out the cream.

735
00:40:27,095 --> 00:40:28,309
(Milk caramel cream, coffee bean cream,)

736
00:40:28,310 --> 00:40:30,093
This time, he has three types.

737
00:40:30,118 --> 00:40:30,978
(and Mascarpone cream)

738
00:40:37,901 --> 00:40:42,224
(He stacks each layer
with sheet cake and cream.)

739
00:40:42,225 --> 00:40:44,110
That's icing right there.

740
00:40:46,677 --> 00:40:49,646
(Wrapping the cake in a crepe)

741
00:40:50,363 --> 00:40:54,518
(The birth of a cute bundle shape)

742
00:40:54,742 --> 00:40:56,386
- It's pretty.
- I agree.

743
00:41:00,507 --> 00:41:03,700
It can be difficult, but deep down,
there's always hope.

744
00:41:04,747 --> 00:41:08,598
I hope that's what they feel
as they eat this.

745
00:41:10,901 --> 00:41:13,437
(Meanwhile, Ji Oh is working
on her tuile.)

746
00:41:14,417 --> 00:41:15,924
The molds are out.

747
00:41:17,150 --> 00:41:22,045
Ji Oh has made a mold for every round.

748
00:41:23,035 --> 00:41:25,035
She's the empress of molds.

749
00:41:26,236 --> 00:41:27,818
It seems she's brought
a whole restaurant arsenal.

750
00:41:28,949 --> 00:41:33,324
I made three kinds of tuile with mugwort
and green tea.

751
00:41:34,391 --> 00:41:35,970
The fall foliage ones are wormwood flavor.

752
00:41:36,215 --> 00:41:37,861
- That's pretty.
- It already looks beautiful.

753
00:41:38,270 --> 00:41:41,965
For the leaves, I wanted to give
them some color variation,

754
00:41:42,224 --> 00:41:47,496
so I made them half green tea
and half mugwort.

755
00:41:47,810 --> 00:41:50,140
She's making a variety of leaves there.

756
00:41:51,142 --> 00:41:55,946
For the persimmon leaves, I made
the outside dark and the center lighter.

757
00:41:56,441 --> 00:41:57,702
For the outside,

758
00:41:57,726 --> 00:42:01,818
I mixed mugwort and green tea
so the color wouldn't pop as much.

759
00:42:02,852 --> 00:42:05,107
For the center, I only used green tea.

760
00:42:07,074 --> 00:42:09,481
It looks like a persimmon leaf.

761
00:42:09,482 --> 00:42:13,330
(Detail that doesn't miss
the minor aspects)

762
00:42:13,438 --> 00:42:14,765
She's incredibly detailed.

763
00:42:14,766 --> 00:42:15,908
(Detail Devil Ji Oh)

764
00:42:15,909 --> 00:42:17,601
That's a work of art.

765
00:42:20,279 --> 00:42:23,673
- She came well prepared.
- She always does.

766
00:42:25,759 --> 00:42:27,759
The persimmon tuile looks delicious.

767
00:42:29,085 --> 00:42:31,885
(The unending, detailed process)

768
00:42:32,059 --> 00:42:33,150
Give me just one.

769
00:42:34,105 --> 00:42:35,619
That's hot!

770
00:42:36,314 --> 00:42:39,489
- She's so detailed!
- Is she shaping each one?

771
00:42:39,788 --> 00:42:41,958
- That's amazing.
- Persimmon leaves usually stick up.

772
00:42:42,373 --> 00:42:43,803
It seems she's shaping each one.

773
00:42:44,761 --> 00:42:46,897
- Is that a detail?
- Yes, they usually curl up.

774
00:42:46,898 --> 00:42:48,765
(Shaping it to look similar
to a real persimmon)

775
00:42:48,992 --> 00:42:51,167
She's bringing out that detail.

776
00:42:51,839 --> 00:42:54,459
She's quite detailed. Amazing.

777
00:42:55,815 --> 00:42:57,474
Nice.

778
00:43:01,060 --> 00:43:02,880
(Impressive visuals)

779
00:43:03,314 --> 00:43:05,067
Ji Oh isn't messing around today.

780
00:43:06,007 --> 00:43:08,251
She's very artistic.

781
00:43:09,240 --> 00:43:10,888
Ji Oh is insane.

782
00:43:12,159 --> 00:43:13,289
What exactly is she?

783
00:43:13,886 --> 00:43:15,392
- Crazy.
- Crazy?

784
00:43:18,315 --> 00:43:19,629
I was wondering what that was.

785
00:43:21,703 --> 00:43:23,566
- What shape is that mold?
- A persimmon, maybe?

786
00:43:25,939 --> 00:43:27,643
- It's a persimmon.
- Persimmon.

787
00:43:27,787 --> 00:43:29,440
Gosh, it's a persimmon.

788
00:43:30,907 --> 00:43:35,412
For the persimmon mold, I bought
the most ideally shaped persimmon...

789
00:43:36,091 --> 00:43:38,484
and used it to make a mold.

790
00:43:39,743 --> 00:43:42,781
- She's going to dunk it.
- It's a persimmon.

791
00:43:49,175 --> 00:43:52,335
I wanted to present it
as a ripe persimmon.

792
00:43:52,637 --> 00:43:54,791
- That looks like a real persimmon.
- That's amazing.

793
00:43:55,334 --> 00:43:58,342
- It looks like a ripe persimmon.
- Impressive.

794
00:43:58,638 --> 00:44:00,972
If you do that half-heartedly,
it'll look lousy.

795
00:44:02,464 --> 00:44:03,136
She's cool.

796
00:44:03,943 --> 00:44:06,944
She's not hesitating.
She knows what she's doing.

797
00:44:08,603 --> 00:44:10,162
It's stunning.

798
00:44:10,163 --> 00:44:12,258
(Will it taste as good as it looks?)

799
00:44:13,235 --> 00:44:15,733
(Gyeong Mu begins the proofing process.)

800
00:44:16,443 --> 00:44:19,076
(He has a serious look on his face.)

801
00:44:19,974 --> 00:44:22,286
There is one hour left in this mission.

802
00:44:23,366 --> 00:44:25,360
You got this!

803
00:44:25,384 --> 00:44:27,510
Hang in there! You got this!

804
00:44:27,511 --> 00:44:32,952
(Other contestants are putting
on their final touches.)

805
00:44:34,519 --> 00:44:36,702
Did Gyeong Mu's pastries go in the oven?

806
00:44:37,186 --> 00:44:38,577
They're in the proofer.

807
00:44:39,779 --> 00:44:41,536
What will he do, then?

808
00:44:41,663 --> 00:44:43,660
He doesn't have much time.
There's only one hour left.

809
00:44:44,948 --> 00:44:48,107
(With 30 minutes needed for proofing,
it's a time crunch to completion.)

810
00:44:48,439 --> 00:44:50,839
For Gyeong Mu,

811
00:44:51,205 --> 00:44:53,271
if he continues that way,
considering time,

812
00:44:54,188 --> 00:44:55,825
the pastry will be underproofed.

813
00:45:00,111 --> 00:45:03,159
(He takes them out of the proofer
to check on them.)

814
00:45:03,246 --> 00:45:05,659
- I'm nervous.
- Extremely.

815
00:45:11,557 --> 00:45:15,224
He's press baking them.
I thought the Taegeukgi would be round.

816
00:45:15,744 --> 00:45:18,221
I guess he's pressing them
to make them flat.

817
00:45:22,029 --> 00:45:23,672
Only 34 minutes.

818
00:45:27,859 --> 00:45:29,019
They're out!

819
00:45:31,013 --> 00:45:33,472
Please be cooked!

820
00:45:34,127 --> 00:45:36,346
(Fortunately, golden brown)

821
00:45:36,600 --> 00:45:37,600
That looks delicious.

822
00:45:38,026 --> 00:45:40,253
- He's coating them.
- He's coating the red ones.

823
00:45:41,779 --> 00:45:43,549
It's strawberry powder and sugar.

824
00:45:44,009 --> 00:45:47,816
(The red drop of the Taegeukgi)

825
00:45:48,610 --> 00:45:52,111
That contestant has only baked one pastry.

826
00:45:52,569 --> 00:45:53,975
- Didn't he have two?
- Yes.

827
00:45:55,115 --> 00:45:56,216
But time...

828
00:45:57,449 --> 00:45:59,517
seems extremely tight.

829
00:45:59,531 --> 00:46:01,297
(Only 30 minutes left
until the end of the round.)

830
00:46:01,384 --> 00:46:02,730
He needs to put them in the oven.

831
00:46:03,327 --> 00:46:05,562
It shouldn't be incomplete.

832
00:46:06,333 --> 00:46:10,350
(The cranberry bean pastry still hasn't
left the proofer.)

833
00:46:10,424 --> 00:46:12,486
They need to be proofed more.

834
00:46:14,096 --> 00:46:15,127
Let's just go!

835
00:46:16,239 --> 00:46:22,469
(The cranberry bean pastry goes
into the oven with 15 minutes left.)

836
00:46:23,342 --> 00:46:24,351
He doesn't have time.

837
00:46:24,698 --> 00:46:26,858
- He really doesn't.
- There's no time.

838
00:46:26,905 --> 00:46:28,271
- Only 13 minutes left.
- It's almost over.

839
00:46:29,220 --> 00:46:30,257
He needs to finish up.

840
00:46:31,291 --> 00:46:32,230
Oh, goodness.

841
00:46:33,450 --> 00:46:35,995
- It's not coming out.
- There's no time.

842
00:46:36,929 --> 00:46:37,953
It needs to be the right color.

843
00:46:39,311 --> 00:46:41,028
- It's still white.
- Is it?

844
00:46:41,594 --> 00:46:43,497
- It's not ready.
- Oh, no.

845
00:46:44,404 --> 00:46:46,003
There's really no time left.

846
00:46:47,070 --> 00:46:48,190
This is frustrating.

847
00:46:50,852 --> 00:46:52,890
Gyeong Mu, you need to take
those pastries out.

848
00:46:53,231 --> 00:46:54,952
There are five minutes left.

849
00:46:56,437 --> 00:46:59,156
I'm nervous.

850
00:47:00,891 --> 00:47:03,922
(The rest of the pastries come out
of the oven with two minutes left.)

851
00:47:04,419 --> 00:47:06,399
- There's no time.
- There are two minutes left.

852
00:47:06,964 --> 00:47:08,541
(Blueberry powder and sugar)

853
00:47:08,601 --> 00:47:11,963
He's even coating on the blue?
That's impressive.

854
00:47:13,196 --> 00:47:15,556
Gyeong Mu, hurry!

855
00:47:15,556 --> 00:47:17,141
(Everyone is praying he makes it.)

856
00:47:17,266 --> 00:47:19,366
One minute left.

857
00:47:19,903 --> 00:47:20,903
Hurry!

858
00:47:23,034 --> 00:47:24,378
Please!

859
00:47:26,551 --> 00:47:29,756
- Run!
- Run!

860
00:47:33,329 --> 00:47:34,346
Only 30 seconds!

861
00:47:34,521 --> 00:47:38,222
(Starts plating with 30 seconds
on the clock)

862
00:47:39,047 --> 00:47:40,794
You got this, Gyeong Mu!

863
00:47:48,804 --> 00:47:56,540
(Finishes by a hair with 8 seconds left)

864
00:47:59,823 --> 00:48:01,842
Well done!

865
00:48:01,911 --> 00:48:07,818
(Final Round 2: Ultimate Pastry ends)

866
00:48:13,277 --> 00:48:15,040
More than feeling relieved
that it was over,

867
00:48:15,957 --> 00:48:18,057
I felt regret.

868
00:48:18,838 --> 00:48:20,701
But it was now or never.

869
00:48:24,172 --> 00:48:25,051
It's over.

870
00:48:28,284 --> 00:48:31,616
The moment I put it down,
I felt a surge of joy.

871
00:48:34,118 --> 00:48:34,866
I'm trembling.

872
00:48:38,410 --> 00:48:39,504
Well done.

873
00:48:47,644 --> 00:48:48,971
It's hard to explain.

874
00:48:49,657 --> 00:48:51,671
It felt like I finished strong.

875
00:48:55,478 --> 00:48:57,084
I think...

876
00:48:58,763 --> 00:49:00,996
I made the pastry that I really wanted
to make.

877
00:49:03,966 --> 00:49:05,546
Since it's the end...

878
00:49:08,238 --> 00:49:09,728
Hold on a second.

879
00:49:09,907 --> 00:49:12,107
This wasn't supposed to happen.
Why am I crying?

880
00:49:20,301 --> 00:49:24,148
You all sprinted towards this moment.

881
00:49:30,658 --> 00:49:35,445
Which pastry will conquer the world?

882
00:49:37,403 --> 00:49:40,263
Your own personal interpretations
of pastries that represent the world,

883
00:49:40,505 --> 00:49:42,338
Seven Ultimate Pastries.

884
00:49:43,787 --> 00:49:46,820
Please reveal them on the stage.

885
00:49:46,927 --> 00:49:48,427
("Ji Oh, you've won everything
but a relationship")

886
00:49:48,574 --> 00:49:49,267
What's going on?

887
00:49:50,894 --> 00:49:52,041
Really?

888
00:50:01,366 --> 00:50:06,000
(Top 7, Ultimate Pastry)

889
00:50:22,300 --> 00:50:24,095
(Kim Si Yeop Lee, Gyeong Mu,
Yoon Hwa Young, Hwang Ji Oh,)

890
00:50:24,119 --> 00:50:25,400
(Ju Yeong Seok, Kim Jin Seo, Seong Min Su)

891
00:50:28,500 --> 00:50:30,300
(Bake Your Dream's Top 7)

892
00:50:30,300 --> 00:50:32,233
They look so cool!

893
00:50:39,533 --> 00:50:44,666
Jeju Blue Ribbon Winner, Kim Si Yeop's
Sea of Dream.

894
00:50:46,600 --> 00:50:51,466
Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu's
Taegeuk Red Bean Pastry.

895
00:50:52,766 --> 00:50:57,566
Fine-Dining Patissier, Yoon Hwa Young's
Mon Pain de Vie.

896
00:50:59,333 --> 00:51:03,900
Crazy Patissiere, Hwang Ji Oh's
Grandmother's Garden.

897
00:51:06,019 --> 00:51:08,652
Pastry Idol, Ju Yeong Seok's...

898
00:51:09,666 --> 00:51:10,633
Black Heart.

899
00:51:13,133 --> 00:51:16,633
Bukhansan Summit Bakery, Kim Jin Seo's...

900
00:51:17,900 --> 00:51:19,433
My Life's Gold Medal.

901
00:51:22,566 --> 00:51:25,766
Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su's...

902
00:51:27,600 --> 00:51:28,433
Mountain.

903
00:51:31,566 --> 00:51:34,733
These are the seven Ultimate Pastries
going out to the world.

904
00:51:38,300 --> 00:51:39,300
For this round,

905
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:43,233
after the top seven are evaluated,

906
00:51:43,533 --> 00:51:46,166
we will announce the final rankings.

907
00:51:49,266 --> 00:51:52,200
As much as this mission was
to birth the Ultimate Pastry,

908
00:51:52,200 --> 00:51:53,400
not only the flavor,

909
00:51:53,400 --> 00:51:55,900
but also the storytelling must be perfect.

910
00:51:56,600 --> 00:52:00,733
The contestants worked
with Korea's top brand marketing expert.

911
00:52:00,733 --> 00:52:02,533
(The Pensive Bodhisattva,
"Room of Quiet Contemplation")

912
00:52:02,533 --> 00:52:04,700
(Led Baekmidang ice cream branding)

913
00:52:04,700 --> 00:52:07,100
(Planned Baekseju's rebranding)

914
00:52:07,100 --> 00:52:09,900
(Branding studio CEO, Kim A Rin)

915
00:52:10,000 --> 00:52:13,300
Flavor and a story.
You all prepared a final dish...

916
00:52:13,300 --> 00:52:15,300
that incorporates these two things.

917
00:52:17,366 --> 00:52:21,033
In the end, with what story...

918
00:52:21,033 --> 00:52:24,166
will the top seven close
out Bake Your Dream?

919
00:52:24,166 --> 00:52:27,133
(Time to present
each of their Ultimate Pastries)

920
00:52:27,433 --> 00:52:30,400
We will reveal them now.

921
00:52:40,800 --> 00:52:46,466
It's time for us to see
Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su's dish.

922
00:52:46,466 --> 00:52:49,333
(Min Su's Ultimate Pastry)

923
00:52:49,333 --> 00:52:51,866
("From Cannoli Prince to Pastry King!")

924
00:52:57,666 --> 00:53:00,366
The dessert I prepared...

925
00:53:01,033 --> 00:53:02,633
is called Mountain.

926
00:53:04,600 --> 00:53:07,500
I think this dessert encapsulates my life.

927
00:53:09,133 --> 00:53:12,266
I believe that not just myself,
but everyone is climbing...

928
00:53:12,266 --> 00:53:16,566
their own mountains called life.

929
00:53:18,766 --> 00:53:21,533
As I dreamed of becoming a pastry chef,

930
00:53:22,400 --> 00:53:25,200
I scaled my own mountain while learning...

931
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:27,233
and striving for 20 years.

932
00:53:30,433 --> 00:53:33,200
Everyone has their ups and downs.

933
00:53:33,500 --> 00:53:36,933
I've also crossed some large mountains
in my day.

934
00:53:38,200 --> 00:53:40,966
When I was a student,
my family was severely struggling.

935
00:53:40,966 --> 00:53:43,800
Our front door was covered
in eviction notices like in the dramas.

936
00:53:46,133 --> 00:53:48,166
When I opened up my first store,

937
00:53:49,133 --> 00:53:52,133
it was when COVID was at its peak.

938
00:53:52,133 --> 00:53:56,400
I couldn't run my store properly
for about a year.

939
00:53:56,400 --> 00:53:57,533
It was a difficult time.

940
00:54:00,400 --> 00:54:02,600
But since I hung in there
and didn't give up,

941
00:54:03,433 --> 00:54:07,300
in the end, wonderful moments came my way.

942
00:54:08,333 --> 00:54:09,733
After crossing those mountains,

943
00:54:10,900 --> 00:54:13,839
I was able to experience those moments.

944
00:54:14,552 --> 00:54:17,400
That's the message I wanted to send.

945
00:54:20,933 --> 00:54:23,533
At our own speeds,

946
00:54:24,033 --> 00:54:26,833
we're all climbing our own mountains.

947
00:54:27,533 --> 00:54:30,233
I think the joys and sorrows we experience
along the way...

948
00:54:30,700 --> 00:54:32,366
represent us all.

949
00:54:33,366 --> 00:54:35,900
I made this dessert with the hope...

950
00:54:37,366 --> 00:54:40,600
that all of us who are climbing
this mountain called life won't give up.

951
00:54:41,700 --> 00:54:43,500
It may be the smallest in the world,

952
00:54:44,733 --> 00:54:48,400
but this mountain containing
all of your dreams...

953
00:54:48,400 --> 00:54:52,266
is the only Ultimate Pastry
that will conquer the world.

954
00:54:52,266 --> 00:54:53,166
Thank You.

955
00:55:04,133 --> 00:55:05,900
That was great storytelling.

956
00:55:06,566 --> 00:55:08,433
Let's commence with the tasting.

957
00:55:08,433 --> 00:55:11,500
(Tasting Min Su's Mountain)

958
00:55:20,700 --> 00:55:23,741
(A Mont Blanc pastry made
with distinct Korean ingredients,)

959
00:55:23,765 --> 00:55:26,000
(including sweet potato,
black raspberry, and Gamhongro.)

960
00:55:26,700 --> 00:55:29,079
(Gamhongro cream, meringue shell,
black raspberry jam,)

961
00:55:29,103 --> 00:55:31,400
(sweet potato mousse, walnut crumble)

962
00:55:32,100 --> 00:55:37,333
(What evaluation will
Min Su's final dessert receive?)

963
00:56:07,600 --> 00:56:10,066
- It's better than when I tasted before.
- Really?

964
00:56:10,733 --> 00:56:11,666
It's better.

965
00:56:17,879 --> 00:56:18,913
This dessert...

966
00:56:20,433 --> 00:56:21,433
as is...

967
00:56:22,100 --> 00:56:26,700
is ready for any restaurant or any hotel.

968
00:56:27,333 --> 00:56:30,600
And it's just as good as it gets.

969
00:56:30,900 --> 00:56:33,266
Hats off and congratulations.

970
00:56:36,366 --> 00:56:42,433
I think the flavor
of the Gamhongro fragrantly meshed well...

971
00:56:42,433 --> 00:56:44,700
with the nuttiness of the sweet potato.

972
00:56:45,866 --> 00:56:48,900
Spreading cocoa butter on the meringue was
a smart choice...

973
00:56:48,900 --> 00:56:53,466
in maintaining the crispiness.

974
00:56:54,533 --> 00:56:56,000
Did the meringue come out well?

975
00:56:56,666 --> 00:56:58,933
By spreading cocoa butter on it,

976
00:56:58,933 --> 00:57:00,766
the meringue won't become soggy.

977
00:57:00,766 --> 00:57:03,366
If it touches the cream,
it will absorb all the moisture.

978
00:57:03,366 --> 00:57:06,400
So he is coating it with cocoa butter.

979
00:57:09,000 --> 00:57:15,333
Looking a bit closer, I could tell
you spent a lot of time...

980
00:57:15,333 --> 00:57:17,033
compactly assembling this dessert
with each layer.

981
00:57:17,033 --> 00:57:21,933
I can see those effort
from the minor details.

982
00:57:22,266 --> 00:57:23,166
Thank you.

983
00:57:24,366 --> 00:57:27,900
I see strength coming from crisis here.

984
00:57:27,900 --> 00:57:29,833
I can also see some aspects
of an adventurer too.

985
00:57:30,333 --> 00:57:33,833
As you placed last
in Round One of the finals,

986
00:57:34,266 --> 00:57:36,866
most people would take a huge gamble...

987
00:57:37,133 --> 00:57:40,700
or just give up altogether.

988
00:57:41,266 --> 00:57:44,381
But for you, Min Su,
in that crisis situation,

989
00:57:44,405 --> 00:57:47,033
you stuck to your own pace...

990
00:57:47,033 --> 00:57:50,900
and seemed to want to clinch
the victory with flavor.

991
00:57:50,900 --> 00:57:52,900
Seeing that, regardless of the results
of this competition,

992
00:57:52,900 --> 00:57:55,633
I'm looking forward to what you can do
in the future.

993
00:57:56,133 --> 00:57:57,833
I think you were
a very impressive contestant.

994
00:58:03,533 --> 00:58:07,066
(Min Su ends with rave reviews.)

995
00:58:07,533 --> 00:58:10,666
All your evaluations are done for the day.

996
00:58:10,666 --> 00:58:11,800
How do you feel?

997
00:58:13,033 --> 00:58:16,466
Until earlier, I felt like I could fly,

998
00:58:17,833 --> 00:58:20,033
but now that I'm here on stage...

999
00:58:23,266 --> 00:58:25,733
I didn't really show it, but...

1000
00:58:26,466 --> 00:58:28,766
as I competed,

1001
00:58:33,100 --> 00:58:35,933
I struggled a lot emotionally.

1002
00:58:50,500 --> 00:58:54,466
I felt very inadequate.

1003
00:59:03,141 --> 00:59:06,841
But since I was able to come
to a fitting conclusion,

1004
00:59:06,866 --> 00:59:09,533
I'm very happy. Thank you.

1005
00:59:12,666 --> 00:59:15,233
Cannoli Prince, Seong Min Su...

1006
00:59:15,233 --> 00:59:17,000
you've done well.

1007
00:59:31,333 --> 00:59:32,433
I have no regrets.

1008
00:59:34,233 --> 00:59:36,633
I did the best I could do.

1009
00:59:37,400 --> 00:59:40,966
This process felt very bitter,

1010
00:59:41,933 --> 00:59:46,433
but the end is quite sweet.

1011
00:59:47,700 --> 00:59:50,766
Next, we will see
Bukhansan Summit Bakery...

1012
00:59:50,766 --> 00:59:54,466
Kim Jin Seo's final dish.

1013
00:59:56,200 --> 00:59:57,600
("Someone who knows what normal is
should judge.")

1014
00:59:57,600 --> 00:59:59,500
The visuals are amazing.

1015
01:00:00,063 --> 01:00:01,429
That's overwhelmingly good.

1016
01:00:01,430 --> 01:00:02,899
That's truly overwhelming.

1017
01:00:07,803 --> 01:00:09,272
So cute.

1018
01:00:11,744 --> 01:00:14,255
(This baby who loved the pastry
has become...)

1019
01:00:14,256 --> 01:00:16,068
- That photo is so cute.
- So cute.

1020
01:00:16,345 --> 01:00:17,680
(a boy who dreamed of Team Korea.)

1021
01:00:17,680 --> 01:00:20,716
My dream was to be
a pastry national representative.

1022
01:00:23,519 --> 01:00:27,089
I wanted to win a medal
and make a name for myself.

1023
01:00:29,525 --> 01:00:32,662
But while preparing for the competition,
I badly injured my hand.

1024
01:00:32,829 --> 01:00:35,064
I couldn't even touch bread.

1025
01:00:35,998 --> 01:00:36,966
(An injury ended his dream.)

1026
01:00:36,967 --> 01:00:38,869
If you give up,
you have to write a pledge.

1027
01:00:38,869 --> 01:00:40,836
That you'll never enter
this competition again.

1028
01:00:41,905 --> 01:00:43,306
That despair back then...

1029
01:00:44,207 --> 01:00:47,043
even turned into resentment
toward my parents.

1030
01:00:52,983 --> 01:00:54,750
But now I know.

1031
01:00:55,319 --> 01:00:56,919
Watching me collapse...

1032
01:00:56,919 --> 01:00:59,121
in front of my dream...

1033
01:00:59,890 --> 01:01:02,657
must've hurt my parents even more.

1034
01:01:02,658 --> 01:01:03,826
(His parents felt guilty.)

1035
01:01:04,427 --> 01:01:06,362
So today,

1036
01:01:07,697 --> 01:01:10,600
I want to place...

1037
01:01:10,867 --> 01:01:12,768
my life's gold medal
around my parents' necks.

1038
01:01:16,740 --> 01:01:18,574
And through that process,

1039
01:01:18,942 --> 01:01:22,278
I learned a valuable lesson.

1040
01:01:22,579 --> 01:01:26,249
"A pastry that carries the baker's heart
can conquer the world."

1041
01:01:29,939 --> 01:01:33,742
A mousse cake holding
both the sweetness and bitterness,

1042
01:01:34,324 --> 01:01:35,892
My Life's Gold Medal.

1043
01:01:36,493 --> 01:01:39,128
This pastry is my Ultimate Pastry.

1044
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:49,772
All right, Bukhansan Summit Bakery,

1045
01:01:49,773 --> 01:01:53,242
Kim Jin Seo, thank you
for your presentation.

1046
01:01:53,610 --> 01:01:55,044
Shall we taste it now?

1047
01:01:56,345 --> 01:01:57,413
The gold medal.

1048
01:01:57,714 --> 01:02:01,817
I captured the taste of a gold medal
in this mousse cake.

1049
01:02:02,251 --> 01:02:06,155
I used banana crème montée
to express its flavor,

1050
01:02:06,656 --> 01:02:10,259
and added caramel crunch
for the rough taste of effort.

1051
01:02:10,727 --> 01:02:13,095
Inside,
there's a strawberry-lime insert...

1052
01:02:13,096 --> 01:02:16,232
to express the refreshing taste
of achievement.

1053
01:02:16,933 --> 01:02:21,337
If you cut through it all at once,
and eat it in its entirety,

1054
01:02:21,671 --> 01:02:25,775
you can taste all its layers.

1055
01:02:46,495 --> 01:02:47,763
That looks delicious.

1056
01:02:48,030 --> 01:02:49,599
They all probably are,
but that one looks the best.

1057
01:02:49,599 --> 01:02:50,699
He really made that well.

1058
01:02:57,040 --> 01:03:01,644
(What will the Masters have to say?)

1059
01:03:05,549 --> 01:03:09,585
Yes, thank you very much
for preparing this dessert.

1060
01:03:09,585 --> 01:03:12,153
The flavors are very fresh.

1061
01:03:12,154 --> 01:03:13,924
And they're all very clear.

1062
01:03:13,924 --> 01:03:16,925
I mean, I can really taste the strawberry,
the banana,

1063
01:03:17,127 --> 01:03:19,495
and the crisp of the base.

1064
01:03:20,796 --> 01:03:22,131
And it's actually very pretty.

1065
01:03:24,734 --> 01:03:28,103
But yes, you did spend a lot of time
on your sugar work.

1066
01:03:28,405 --> 01:03:33,409
And I'm not sure that's really
the focus of this competition.

1067
01:03:33,743 --> 01:03:35,578
Something for you to keep in mind.

1068
01:03:35,578 --> 01:03:36,679
So, thank you.

1069
01:03:38,515 --> 01:03:40,550
A craftsman's hands,

1070
01:03:41,184 --> 01:03:43,286
they say, are the blade of one's thoughts.

1071
01:03:44,021 --> 01:03:46,222
What kind of thoughts...

1072
01:03:46,656 --> 01:03:48,558
and what kind of mindset you carry...

1073
01:03:48,725 --> 01:03:51,360
determines the final product.

1074
01:03:53,396 --> 01:03:55,598
But from the very start,

1075
01:03:56,299 --> 01:03:58,534
I wonder if your thinking was
a little off.

1076
01:04:01,871 --> 01:04:05,474
Shouldn't flavor come first,
then the look?

1077
01:04:06,042 --> 01:04:07,376
That's what I think.

1078
01:04:07,376 --> 01:04:09,078
(A harsh critique
from Master Kim Young Mo)

1079
01:04:11,948 --> 01:04:16,219
I actually share a similar story
with you, Jin Seo.

1080
01:04:18,688 --> 01:04:21,724
I also couldn't go
to the WorldSkills Competition.

1081
01:04:22,626 --> 01:04:28,297
After that, I felt the same emotions
you're feeling now,

1082
01:04:28,698 --> 01:04:30,867
including resentment
about my financial situation.

1083
01:04:30,867 --> 01:04:32,935
A lot happened.

1084
01:04:33,703 --> 01:04:37,940
But I think you need
to come out of that pain.

1085
01:04:37,940 --> 01:04:40,442
(You need to come out of that pain.)

1086
01:04:41,945 --> 01:04:44,614
When I taste this dessert,

1087
01:04:44,614 --> 01:04:48,784
it tastes like the kind of desserts
I made when I was 25.

1088
01:04:50,153 --> 01:04:53,789
I understand your story and your thoughts.

1089
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:55,458
But when I taste it,

1090
01:04:55,458 --> 01:04:56,659
(Got caught up in his story.)

1091
01:04:56,659 --> 01:04:59,027
it doesn't really feel delicious.

1092
01:04:59,128 --> 01:05:01,230
That happened years ago already.

1093
01:05:01,230 --> 01:05:03,966
Rather than dwelling on the past,

1094
01:05:03,966 --> 01:05:07,570
what matters now is moving on.

1095
01:05:08,304 --> 01:05:09,505
As someone who's been through it.

1096
01:05:10,106 --> 01:05:11,941
I believe in you, Jin Seo.

1097
01:05:11,941 --> 01:05:14,744
You can do even better.

1098
01:05:15,144 --> 01:05:17,478
And I truly hope things go well for you.

1099
01:05:17,480 --> 01:05:19,048
I'll be sincerely rooting for you.

1100
01:05:19,048 --> 01:05:21,384
(Na Rae cheers him on
with heartfelt advice.)

1101
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,689
This is actually off the record, but...

1102
01:05:27,924 --> 01:05:29,926
(More from Sung Jun?)

1103
01:05:29,926 --> 01:05:31,093
Later on...

1104
01:05:31,294 --> 01:05:33,863
you're still young, after all.

1105
01:05:34,497 --> 01:05:36,999
(Pardon?)

1106
01:05:37,133 --> 01:05:40,236
If you'd ever like to work
in a restaurant,

1107
01:05:43,806 --> 01:05:46,842
I'd appreciate it if you sent me a DM.

1108
01:05:47,777 --> 01:05:50,580
First, I'll go to the restaurant...

1109
01:05:50,580 --> 01:05:53,115
and try the food.

1110
01:05:53,449 --> 01:05:55,416
(Nice comeback.)

1111
01:05:57,486 --> 01:05:59,388
(Shocked)

1112
01:05:59,689 --> 01:06:00,690
(Surprised)

1113
01:06:00,690 --> 01:06:01,820
Now that's bold.

1114
01:06:01,820 --> 01:06:03,592
(He shows the bold spirit
of his generation.)

1115
01:06:06,762 --> 01:06:10,900
(What'll happen to Sung Jun's pick,
My Life's Gold Medal?)

1116
01:06:11,901 --> 01:06:14,270
Next up is Pastry Idol,

1117
01:06:14,270 --> 01:06:17,440
Ju Yeong Seok with his entry.

1118
01:06:17,707 --> 01:06:19,508
("Ju Yeong Seok, my forever Pastry Idol.")

1119
01:06:20,543 --> 01:06:22,111
(What is Ju Yeong Seok's dish?)

1120
01:06:22,111 --> 01:06:23,145
That's cool.

1121
01:06:28,551 --> 01:06:29,986
(Oh?)

1122
01:06:41,430 --> 01:06:45,568
(Yeong Seok looks very different now
from then.)

1123
01:06:47,504 --> 01:06:49,038
Back in my twenties,

1124
01:06:49,038 --> 01:06:52,074
I worked as an idol in Japan,
far from home.

1125
01:06:52,375 --> 01:06:55,912
(Yeong Seok debuted in 2008
with the idol group SMASH.)

1126
01:06:56,445 --> 01:06:58,881
Back then, the language
and culture were foreign, and I was alone.

1127
01:06:59,448 --> 01:07:01,483
I had a cream bun
from a convenience store,

1128
01:07:02,017 --> 01:07:04,520
and it felt like I'd made it
through the day.

1129
01:07:04,520 --> 01:07:06,288
It was comforting.

1130
01:07:07,156 --> 01:07:08,691
After my idol career ended,

1131
01:07:09,425 --> 01:07:12,861
I became a baker to make a living.

1132
01:07:13,729 --> 01:07:16,232
That cream bun then...

1133
01:07:16,232 --> 01:07:19,168
felt completely different
from the comfort it once gave me.

1134
01:07:22,972 --> 01:07:24,173
It was a second career...

1135
01:07:24,607 --> 01:07:27,910
and the work that kept me going.

1136
01:07:30,613 --> 01:07:32,949
It wasn't easy,

1137
01:07:33,482 --> 01:07:36,419
but I wanted to leave the message...

1138
01:07:36,819 --> 01:07:38,754
of not letting go of hope.

1139
01:07:40,290 --> 01:07:42,725
Just as white cream once comforted...

1140
01:07:42,858 --> 01:07:44,760
my dark days,

1141
01:07:45,328 --> 01:07:48,297
I wanted to hold both dark and light.

1142
01:07:49,833 --> 01:07:53,635
Black rice's nutty flavor is
still unfamiliar worldwide.

1143
01:07:54,570 --> 01:07:57,974
So I layered caramel and coffee cream.

1144
01:07:57,974 --> 01:08:00,176
(Caramel and coffee cream
for a balanced flavor.)

1145
01:08:00,810 --> 01:08:04,647
By finding interest in familiarity,

1146
01:08:05,481 --> 01:08:08,150
I believe this can grow into...

1147
01:08:08,551 --> 01:08:10,886
a global dessert.

1148
01:08:13,623 --> 01:08:15,960
With my Ultimate Pastry, Black Heart,

1149
01:08:16,259 --> 01:08:17,860
in an uncertain future,

1150
01:08:18,327 --> 01:08:21,731
to all those quietly enduring each day,

1151
01:08:22,932 --> 01:08:24,901
once you pass through a dark tunnel,

1152
01:08:24,901 --> 01:08:28,270
someday, like sweet white cream...

1153
01:08:28,504 --> 01:08:30,473
gift-like moments will come.

1154
01:08:30,473 --> 01:08:32,641
I wanted to share that hope.

1155
01:08:46,489 --> 01:08:48,524
Then, let's taste his pastry.

1156
01:08:49,459 --> 01:08:51,160
Cute.

1157
01:08:53,496 --> 01:08:55,364
There are three creams,

1158
01:08:55,665 --> 01:08:58,534
but black rice is the key.

1159
01:08:59,368 --> 01:09:03,005
It adds crunch beneath that softness...

1160
01:09:03,339 --> 01:09:05,374
and a nutty flavor.

1161
01:09:05,374 --> 01:09:07,109
(Black Heart, rich with nutty flavor)

1162
01:09:18,321 --> 01:09:24,927
(How will the Masters judge it?)

1163
01:09:29,899 --> 01:09:32,969
You did well because in the end,
it looks really good.

1164
01:09:33,302 --> 01:09:36,939
Presentation is well done.
I really like the look. It's great.

1165
01:09:37,307 --> 01:09:41,777
I think the usage of the black rice saved
your dessert.

1166
01:09:42,912 --> 01:09:46,148
Why? Because I think it's something
that really brings texture.

1167
01:09:46,148 --> 01:09:49,485
It's really something very interesting.
I really enjoy eating that black rice.

1168
01:09:49,852 --> 01:09:53,189
Overall, it's a good dessert.

1169
01:09:53,623 --> 01:09:55,157
In terms of texture,

1170
01:09:55,157 --> 01:09:58,394
I would like to have maybe something
a little bit more sour inside.

1171
01:09:59,229 --> 01:10:02,932
But again, it's a good job
and I'm glad it represents you.

1172
01:10:04,031 --> 01:10:05,806
You're indeed the prince of cream.

1173
01:10:07,215 --> 01:10:11,945
I could taste all the flavors layered
together, and it was really enjoyable.

1174
01:10:13,035 --> 01:10:17,661
The black rice was sweet and salty.

1175
01:10:17,662 --> 01:10:22,356
I really enjoyed the combination
of both flavors.

1176
01:10:23,946 --> 01:10:26,613
I thought...

1177
01:10:27,072 --> 01:10:30,498
it was visually really beautiful,

1178
01:10:31,239 --> 01:10:35,836
but I wished it had more cream.

1179
01:10:35,969 --> 01:10:40,261
If cream were added on the outside,

1180
01:10:40,288 --> 01:10:44,307
it could add moisture to the crepe
and make it softer.

1181
01:10:44,720 --> 01:10:47,513
I think that would've been better.

1182
01:10:47,514 --> 01:10:52,519
But visually, I fell in love with it.

1183
01:10:54,188 --> 01:10:59,193
I realized at the end
that it needed more layers of cream.

1184
01:10:59,485 --> 01:11:01,562
I used fewer sheets than I had planned.

1185
01:11:01,563 --> 01:11:04,044
(Yeong Seok added fewer sheets
than planned.)

1186
01:11:04,045 --> 01:11:07,134
I realized it when I was done.

1187
01:11:08,227 --> 01:11:13,207
I wanted to impress them in the finals,
but ended up making a mistake.

1188
01:11:15,615 --> 01:11:17,428
We're halfway through already.

1189
01:11:19,908 --> 01:11:25,853
Next up is Crazy Patissiere,
Hwang Ji Oh's Ultimate Pastry.

1190
01:11:26,527 --> 01:11:28,294
(Hwang Ji Oh's Ultimate Pastry)

1191
01:11:28,295 --> 01:11:29,590
Ji Oh is on fire!

1192
01:11:35,718 --> 01:11:39,565
(The Ultimate Pastry made by Hwang Ji Oh)

1193
01:11:39,566 --> 01:11:40,968
That looks nice.

1194
01:11:48,489 --> 01:11:50,111
That must be her grandma.

1195
01:11:59,306 --> 01:12:01,255
Her grandma used to give her persimmons.

1196
01:12:02,232 --> 01:12:06,927
My first dessert ever was
in my grandma's yard.

1197
01:12:07,761 --> 01:12:12,099
The sweetness of the fruit she grew
with love and care...

1198
01:12:13,096 --> 01:12:17,304
still feels like the perfect dessert
to me.

1199
01:12:17,562 --> 01:12:21,175
Her yard was humble yet abundant,

1200
01:12:21,588 --> 01:12:25,614
and it gave me the nourishment
I needed as a person...

1201
01:12:25,914 --> 01:12:27,648
and the roots I needed
to grow into a patissiere.

1202
01:12:30,644 --> 01:12:35,167
The flavor filled with my grandmother's
love is the most Korean,

1203
01:12:35,379 --> 01:12:38,692
and it has the power to reach the world.

1204
01:12:40,127 --> 01:12:44,665
The Ultimate Pastry I made is called
"Grandma's Yard."

1205
01:12:47,267 --> 01:12:49,870
(Grandma's Yard)

1206
01:12:49,924 --> 01:12:53,070
There was a tree in full bloom.

1207
01:12:54,843 --> 01:12:57,356
And there's a persimmon underneath.

1208
01:12:58,050 --> 01:13:02,149
On the bottom,
I put a persimmon-flavored sablé...

1209
01:13:02,782 --> 01:13:07,541
and leaf-shaped pastries
to depict the yard...

1210
01:13:07,701 --> 01:13:10,190
with a fallen persimmon.

1211
01:13:17,746 --> 01:13:19,466
Her first dessert in life.

1212
01:13:25,678 --> 01:13:29,390
Break open the persimmon-shaped mousse...

1213
01:13:30,144 --> 01:13:34,510
and scoop up the compote
with some cream first.

1214
01:13:34,783 --> 01:13:37,051
You'll really taste the persimmon
that way.

1215
01:13:37,351 --> 01:13:40,595
And there's Jatbaksan underneath.

1216
01:13:41,089 --> 01:13:45,493
I made the traditional Korean sweets
with pine nuts into a sablé.

1217
01:13:45,767 --> 01:13:49,463
If you eat them together,
it's even more enjoyable.

1218
01:14:21,535 --> 01:14:22,535
Is it good?

1219
01:14:24,634 --> 01:14:26,454
It has a nice fruity smell.
It's delicious.

1220
01:14:32,900 --> 01:14:36,076
- I like the idea.
- The tuiles are good too.

1221
01:14:37,332 --> 01:14:39,279
They taste like green tea and mugwort.

1222
01:14:42,738 --> 01:14:45,711
What do you think it is that could make...

1223
01:14:45,712 --> 01:14:49,122
this product take over the world?

1224
01:14:49,824 --> 01:14:53,531
In the countryside,
you can easily see persimmon trees.

1225
01:14:53,950 --> 01:14:58,899
You know, in Korea,
we have a concept called "Jeong."

1226
01:14:59,967 --> 01:15:02,540
If you look at a persimmon tree,

1227
01:15:02,741 --> 01:15:06,406
people often leave a few persimmons
on the tree for magpies to eat.

1228
01:15:06,780 --> 01:15:10,677
I wanted to capture that kind of image
to promote Korea.

1229
01:15:11,011 --> 01:15:16,783
I also tried to include
as many Korean elements as possible.

1230
01:15:17,058 --> 01:15:20,053
I used traditional Korean desserts
for the sablé.

1231
01:15:20,650 --> 01:15:24,663
They're rice puffs made with pine nuts
called Jatbaksan.

1232
01:15:25,750 --> 01:15:30,029
I realized they tasted really good
with dried persimmons.

1233
01:15:32,322 --> 01:15:35,389
So I used dried persimmons
and soft persimmons...

1234
01:15:35,661 --> 01:15:38,304
to make it as Korean as possible.

1235
01:15:39,174 --> 01:15:42,909
When I do interviews in France,

1236
01:15:44,090 --> 01:15:48,293
one of the most common questions
I get is, "What are Korean desserts?"

1237
01:15:48,346 --> 01:15:53,086
My usual answer is "seasonal fruits."

1238
01:15:53,699 --> 01:15:56,423
I think you did a great job
using Korean ingredients.

1239
01:15:56,777 --> 01:16:00,260
The textures of soft persimmon
and sweet persimmon...

1240
01:16:00,770 --> 01:16:03,496
really stood out.

1241
01:16:03,664 --> 01:16:07,868
Great work today.
I really enjoyed your dessert.

1242
01:16:08,609 --> 01:16:10,909
You seem to know what to do
throughout the whole process.

1243
01:16:11,843 --> 01:16:15,142
I loved all the details.
You bent the tuiles...

1244
01:16:15,456 --> 01:16:17,972
to make the green top on the persimmon.

1245
01:16:20,664 --> 01:16:24,588
I really wanted to recreate
the look of fallen leaves.

1246
01:16:26,093 --> 01:16:29,756
I wanted the tree to have a textured look.

1247
01:16:29,978 --> 01:16:31,191
It has a lot of details.

1248
01:16:31,807 --> 01:16:34,528
Persimmons aren't perfectly shaped.

1249
01:16:35,362 --> 01:16:36,621
Look at that!

1250
01:16:36,622 --> 01:16:39,107
Those details look so natural.

1251
01:16:39,594 --> 01:16:43,490
All these small details make a difference.
You're really on top of it.

1252
01:16:43,610 --> 01:16:45,796
You've really mastered it.

1253
01:16:46,582 --> 01:16:52,445
It's not too sweet. It's well-balanced.
Great work. Well done.

1254
01:16:56,757 --> 01:17:02,476
I believe a dessert should be easy to eat,
even when you're full.

1255
01:17:02,477 --> 01:17:03,321
(Agreed.)

1256
01:17:04,337 --> 01:17:07,227
And your cake today...

1257
01:17:11,668 --> 01:17:13,233
was that kind of cake to me.

1258
01:17:15,895 --> 01:17:21,241
For shape, flavor, concept, story,
and product value,

1259
01:17:22,340 --> 01:17:26,079
I gave you the perfect score.
I really enjoyed it.

1260
01:17:26,779 --> 01:17:28,918
(Seok Won's high praise)

1261
01:17:28,919 --> 01:17:29,919
Thank you.

1262
01:17:35,157 --> 01:17:36,556
The perfect score.

1263
01:17:37,324 --> 01:17:39,664
It looks like
the rankings are going to change.

1264
01:17:40,316 --> 01:17:43,256
The perfect score is 600 in Round 1
and 800 in Round 2.

1265
01:17:43,930 --> 01:17:45,044
That's true.

1266
01:17:45,045 --> 01:17:46,867
(The rankings can change easily.)

1267
01:17:47,243 --> 01:17:50,270
(Yoon Hwa Young,
3rd place in Round 1 of the finals)

1268
01:17:51,172 --> 01:17:54,841
(Lee Gyeong Mu,
2nd place in Round 1 of the finals)

1269
01:17:55,385 --> 01:17:58,245
(Kim Si Yeop,
1st place in Round 1 of the finals)

1270
01:17:59,411 --> 01:18:01,411
(Will there be a twist?)

1271
01:18:02,402 --> 01:18:05,519
Next up is Fine-Dining Patissier.

1272
01:18:05,649 --> 01:18:08,921
Let's meet Yoon Hwa Young's
Ultimate Pastry.

1273
01:18:09,189 --> 01:18:10,957
(Only one round is left
for the deity, Hwa Young.)

1274
01:18:11,893 --> 01:18:16,829
Good health starts with eating good food.

1275
01:18:16,952 --> 01:18:18,731
I hope...

1276
01:18:19,239 --> 01:18:21,568
everyone who eats my bread stays healthy,

1277
01:18:22,018 --> 01:18:25,271
so I made a sugar-free pain de campagne.

1278
01:18:27,471 --> 01:18:31,678
I've always been interested
in healthy food and bread...

1279
01:18:32,261 --> 01:18:33,680
because of my family history.

1280
01:18:35,761 --> 01:18:40,788
(Hwa Young makes healthy bread
because of his family.)

1281
01:18:42,189 --> 01:18:43,390
My grandfather passed away...

1282
01:18:44,819 --> 01:18:47,127
from complications of diabetes
and Parkinson's,

1283
01:18:48,158 --> 01:18:50,297
and my mom has diabetes.

1284
01:18:52,651 --> 01:18:55,902
That's why my Ultimate Pastry is bread...

1285
01:18:56,337 --> 01:19:00,240
that my family and I can enjoy
for the rest of our lives.

1286
01:19:02,889 --> 01:19:06,413
So I made this bread called
"Mon Pain de Vie."

1287
01:19:07,255 --> 01:19:10,854
In French,
it means "the bread of my life."

1288
01:19:11,574 --> 01:19:15,037
People of all ages and genders
can enjoy it all year round.

1289
01:19:15,257 --> 01:19:19,836
Mon Pain de Vie is the bread
that will take over the world.

1290
01:19:27,895 --> 01:19:31,405
First, give Mon Pain de Vie a sniff.

1291
01:19:32,481 --> 01:19:34,481
Just as we enjoy side dishes,

1292
01:19:34,747 --> 01:19:39,245
I wanted to make four accompaniments
for the bread.

1293
01:19:40,306 --> 01:19:41,718
I made kelp butter.

1294
01:19:45,648 --> 01:19:48,255
I also included hummus and carrot râpée.

1295
01:19:50,914 --> 01:19:52,960
It comes with egg salad and avocado too.

1296
01:19:56,116 --> 01:19:58,498
There's also apple compote
and fromage blanc.

1297
01:20:01,466 --> 01:20:03,133
Shall we taste the bread?

1298
01:20:12,433 --> 01:20:15,400
You usually eat table bread
with butter, right?

1299
01:20:15,400 --> 01:20:19,533
Please spread a little kelp butter
on the first piece at the bottom.

1300
01:20:22,333 --> 01:20:24,566
(A bite with kelp butter first)

1301
01:20:30,933 --> 01:20:36,533
Second, there are hummus
and carrot râpée as an appetizer.

1302
01:20:45,733 --> 01:20:47,033
Then for today's main,

1303
01:20:47,033 --> 01:20:50,700
top it with egg salad and avocado
for the best bite.

1304
01:20:59,233 --> 01:21:04,700
And for dessert, the apple compote
with the fromage blanc...

1305
01:21:04,700 --> 01:21:07,433
lets you enjoy it all
in a single bread course.

1306
01:21:07,433 --> 01:21:08,333
Apple.

1307
01:21:22,600 --> 01:21:23,866
The bread is nutty.

1308
01:21:24,600 --> 01:21:26,666
I think the perilla seeds
make it even nuttier.

1309
01:21:27,000 --> 01:21:30,933
More than the other breads,
he seems devoted to sourdough.

1310
01:21:33,200 --> 01:21:35,133
- The bread is good, right?
- It is.

1311
01:21:35,133 --> 01:21:36,533
It's my favorite.

1312
01:21:39,733 --> 01:21:41,800
(Master Noh Hee Young's comments?)

1313
01:21:42,600 --> 01:21:45,133
Wherever I go, when people ask
what my favorite bread is,

1314
01:21:45,133 --> 01:21:47,466
I confidently say it's pain de campagne.

1315
01:21:47,466 --> 01:21:50,833
It's known as an easy-to-digest bread,

1316
01:21:50,833 --> 01:21:53,833
It's made with natural fermentation,
so it's really good for you.

1317
01:21:53,833 --> 01:21:55,700
I think it was an excellent choice.

1318
01:21:55,700 --> 01:22:00,466
Today, this kelp butter went
so well with the sourdough.

1319
01:22:00,933 --> 01:22:06,833
And you prepared the other items.

1320
01:22:06,833 --> 01:22:10,933
I thought it was
a wonderful French course.

1321
01:22:10,933 --> 01:22:11,733
Thank you.

1322
01:22:14,833 --> 01:22:17,300
Overall, I liked very much the bread.

1323
01:22:17,300 --> 01:22:19,633
The crust was well developed.

1324
01:22:19,633 --> 01:22:22,166
And I think this is really the Korean way.

1325
01:22:22,166 --> 01:22:27,533
Right? With a variety
of textures and flavors.

1326
01:22:27,533 --> 01:22:30,600
And I think it's expressed
in a great way...

1327
01:22:30,600 --> 01:22:35,366
how European bread can be used
in a very Korean way.

1328
01:22:35,366 --> 01:22:38,433
For me, there are a few of them...

1329
01:22:38,433 --> 01:22:39,633
a bit overpowering.

1330
01:22:42,103 --> 01:22:46,033
Especially, the hummus
with the carrot râpées.

1331
01:22:49,500 --> 01:22:54,966
This is the second time
you've presented pain de campagne.

1332
01:22:54,966 --> 01:22:55,900
That's right.

1333
01:22:55,900 --> 01:22:59,633
In France, they say it has
a starter's signature flavor.

1334
01:22:59,633 --> 01:23:02,466
Because every house's starter
tastes different.

1335
01:23:02,466 --> 01:23:07,100
Your starter didn't have much tang,

1336
01:23:07,100 --> 01:23:09,500
and it had a very nutty flavor.

1337
01:23:09,500 --> 01:23:13,433
By adding perilla seeds
to that starter flavor,

1338
01:23:13,433 --> 01:23:16,400
You brought out more nuttiness.

1339
01:23:16,400 --> 01:23:19,633
I really liked that perilla seed note.

1340
01:23:19,633 --> 01:23:22,833
What was a bit disappointing...

1341
01:23:24,600 --> 01:23:28,266
was that I think bread
should remain bread.

1342
01:23:28,266 --> 01:23:30,566
So the cheese felt a little disappointing.

1343
01:23:32,733 --> 01:23:35,300
Shall I give you a native Korean take?

1344
01:23:37,000 --> 01:23:39,400
I saw it a bit differently.

1345
01:23:39,866 --> 01:23:44,100
The Emmental cheese came through.

1346
01:23:44,100 --> 01:23:46,866
And that slight salty note...

1347
01:23:46,866 --> 01:23:50,191
made the bread tasty
even without extra seasoning.

1348
01:23:50,633 --> 01:23:53,766
Koreans love nutty flavor.

1349
01:23:53,766 --> 01:23:56,800
I think you brought it out well
in pain de campagne.

1350
01:23:56,800 --> 01:23:58,500
And I really enjoyed it today.

1351
01:23:58,500 --> 01:23:59,533
Thank you.

1352
01:23:59,533 --> 01:24:00,400
Thank you.

1353
01:24:05,033 --> 01:24:09,033
In Young, you competed
with Hwa Young in Round Two.

1354
01:24:09,033 --> 01:24:10,800
How's it been being together here?

1355
01:24:11,333 --> 01:24:12,233
Oh no.

1356
01:24:15,666 --> 01:24:17,933
I'm about to cry again. What do I do?

1357
01:24:22,000 --> 01:24:26,033
When I was eliminated, in my interview,

1358
01:24:26,033 --> 01:24:31,400
the last thing I said was,
"Chef Hwa Young, please win."

1359
01:24:31,700 --> 01:24:34,833
But today, you did so well.

1360
01:24:35,266 --> 01:24:37,400
It feels like I'm watching my dad.

1361
01:24:38,733 --> 01:24:41,700
I'm so proud and moved.

1362
01:24:41,700 --> 01:24:43,600
- You can do it.
- Let's go.

1363
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:46,066
- Dopamine, let's go.
- Dopamine, let's go.

1364
01:24:48,500 --> 01:24:52,766
Fine-Dining Patissier, Yoon Hwa Young,
you've worked so hard.

1365
01:24:54,133 --> 01:24:56,100
Thank you. Great work.

1366
01:24:56,100 --> 01:24:58,400
All right, please move on
to the Top Seven zone.

1367
01:24:58,400 --> 01:24:59,566
Great work.

1368
01:25:00,633 --> 01:25:02,500
Great work. That was excellent.

1369
01:25:12,766 --> 01:25:15,666
(The emotions surge in
after the final presentation.)

1370
01:25:15,666 --> 01:25:19,166
I wasn't here to compete with anyone,
but to compete with myself.

1371
01:25:19,166 --> 01:25:21,633
I wanted to hear
how my work would be judged.

1372
01:25:21,633 --> 01:25:23,633
I thought,
"They're giving me such high praise?"

1373
01:25:23,633 --> 01:25:26,600
I was overwhelmed.

1374
01:25:27,266 --> 01:25:30,491
Next, let's take a look
at Dessert Macho Lee Gyeong Mu's...

1375
01:25:30,491 --> 01:25:32,526
Ultimate Pastry.

1376
01:25:33,766 --> 01:25:34,966
(Do you know K-bread?)

1377
01:25:34,966 --> 01:25:36,200
Do you know K-bread?

1378
01:25:37,266 --> 01:25:40,000
Hello, I'm Dessert Macho, Lee Gyeong Mu.

1379
01:25:40,633 --> 01:25:42,966
(What story is Lee Gyeong Mu telling
through K-bread?)

1380
01:25:45,666 --> 01:25:47,466
Back when I knew nothing about bread,

1381
01:25:47,966 --> 01:25:50,733
the first bread I ever made
was red bean bread.

1382
01:25:52,266 --> 01:25:54,933
When I was hungry,
I'd secretly take a bite...

1383
01:25:54,933 --> 01:25:56,966
of red bean bread to get through the day.

1384
01:25:56,966 --> 01:25:58,466
(It got him through hard times.)

1385
01:26:00,033 --> 01:26:03,833
For me, red bean bread was
what got me through life.

1386
01:26:04,700 --> 01:26:09,266
(It also became the starting point
of his rise on the world stage.)

1387
01:26:10,400 --> 01:26:14,800
But ironically,
this meaningful red bean bread...

1388
01:26:14,800 --> 01:26:17,566
couldn't be found in the global market.

1389
01:26:17,966 --> 01:26:19,333
So I made up my mind.

1390
01:26:19,900 --> 01:26:21,566
It's familiar to us,

1391
01:26:21,566 --> 01:26:23,700
but this red bean bread is still
unfamiliar to the world.

1392
01:26:24,400 --> 01:26:26,766
I wanted to make it a bread
that the world would seek out first.

1393
01:26:27,766 --> 01:26:33,133
That's why I made Taegeuk Red Bean Bread.

1394
01:26:36,200 --> 01:26:37,800
(Do you know K-red beans?)

1395
01:26:37,800 --> 01:26:39,433
Do you know K-red beans?

1396
01:26:41,000 --> 01:26:42,133
Do you know K-red beans?

1397
01:26:43,166 --> 01:26:44,833
- I know!
- Starting now...

1398
01:26:44,833 --> 01:26:46,800
please experience
my very own Ultimate Pastry,

1399
01:26:46,800 --> 01:26:49,066
Taegeuk Red Bean Bread.

1400
01:26:49,066 --> 01:26:51,833
(Taegeuk Red Bean Bread)

1401
01:26:52,233 --> 01:26:54,466
What's the best way to eat this bread?

1402
01:26:54,466 --> 01:27:00,100
The bread on top represents
omegi red beans.

1403
01:27:00,100 --> 01:27:04,066
And inside, I added a cream
made with beans and corn.

1404
01:27:04,066 --> 01:27:07,366
Please eat the center
of the top bread first.

1405
01:27:07,366 --> 01:27:10,633
For the bottom bread,
I used cranberry beans and ginger...

1406
01:27:10,633 --> 01:27:12,633
with a mild note of Hallabong.

1407
01:27:12,633 --> 01:27:16,800
I've incorporated every recipe
I've made on this show.

1408
01:27:18,200 --> 01:27:19,633
The Taegeuk flag.

1409
01:27:20,366 --> 01:27:21,300
Cute.

1410
01:27:59,000 --> 01:28:05,600
(Can it win over the world, as he hopes?)

1411
01:28:15,833 --> 01:28:19,033
Why did you use
dry red beans and rice cake...

1412
01:28:19,033 --> 01:28:23,033
to express omegi-tteok?

1413
01:28:24,600 --> 01:28:27,800
Since red bean bread
originally came from Japan,

1414
01:28:27,800 --> 01:28:31,433
I thought about how to express
red beans in a Korean way.

1415
01:28:31,433 --> 01:28:34,633
First thing came to my mind was
red beans from omegi-tteok.

1416
01:28:34,633 --> 01:28:38,900
I made a cream with beans
to make it less dry.

1417
01:28:38,900 --> 01:28:43,933
I used to buy red bean bread
at Japanese bakeries in Paris too.

1418
01:28:43,933 --> 01:28:46,733
Because there were no Korean bakeries.

1419
01:28:46,733 --> 01:28:52,300
The theme of taking red bean bread global
really resonated with me.

1420
01:28:52,300 --> 01:28:56,633
Even though you could've prepared
things in advance,

1421
01:28:56,633 --> 01:29:01,366
you carefully made everything
from the filling up.

1422
01:29:01,366 --> 01:29:04,000
Thank you. I really enjoyed it.

1423
01:29:04,000 --> 01:29:05,033
Great work.

1424
01:29:09,100 --> 01:29:12,166
The tastes are good, but for me...

1425
01:29:14,900 --> 01:29:17,533
the red bean one, especially,
is a bit dry.

1426
01:29:20,000 --> 01:29:22,800
More attention on the overall filling.

1427
01:29:22,800 --> 01:29:25,966
But overall,
I enjoyed the dessert very well.

1428
01:29:25,966 --> 01:29:29,933
(The fillings in the bread fell short.)

1429
01:29:30,633 --> 01:29:37,266
I think you might not have focused
on the right things today.

1430
01:29:40,300 --> 01:29:44,066
Since you used a cercle
to create the taegeuk pattern,

1431
01:29:44,066 --> 01:29:45,933
the side color didn't come through well.

1432
01:29:47,100 --> 01:29:50,533
Then you should've removed the ring mold
and added more color afterward.

1433
01:29:50,900 --> 01:29:52,566
But you couldn't do that.

1434
01:29:52,566 --> 01:29:54,066
Because you ran out of time.

1435
01:29:54,066 --> 01:29:57,366
So the sides caved in,

1436
01:29:57,366 --> 01:30:02,240
and that likely dried out the filling too.

1437
01:30:02,265 --> 01:30:06,269
You did an amazing job today,
but it could've been better.

1438
01:30:06,269 --> 01:30:07,670
It's my fault.

1439
01:30:07,670 --> 01:30:12,008
I wanted to show everything I've got
in this competition,

1440
01:30:12,208 --> 01:30:14,443
and I got carried away.

1441
01:30:14,911 --> 01:30:17,880
(What will the final outcome
of this pastry be?)

1442
01:30:18,281 --> 01:30:21,317
Jeju Blue Ribbon Winner, Kim Si Yeop.

1443
01:30:21,317 --> 01:30:23,586
Let's meet his Ultimate Pastry.

1444
01:30:25,688 --> 01:30:27,924
(Si Yeop is currently in 1st place
with 556 points.)

1445
01:30:35,331 --> 01:30:38,434
It looks different set up like that.

1446
01:30:45,139 --> 01:30:47,174
- What is that?
- A water drop.

1447
01:30:48,244 --> 01:30:51,614
My Ultimate Pastry is called
"Si Yeop's Dream."

1448
01:30:53,115 --> 01:30:55,585
This pastry holds all the dreams, passion,

1449
01:30:55,585 --> 01:31:00,523
and tears of the people I met
during the competition.

1450
01:31:04,727 --> 01:31:07,363
The tears she shed thinking of her son.

1451
01:31:08,931 --> 01:31:15,805
(In Young cried, thinking about her son.)

1452
01:31:17,473 --> 01:31:20,910
Im Hoon's bittersweet tears
over his signature bread.

1453
01:31:21,457 --> 01:31:25,414
(Im Hoon cried over his love-hate feelings
for his cream bread.)

1454
01:31:25,915 --> 01:31:28,517
Jung Hoon's tears of joy...

1455
01:31:28,517 --> 01:31:31,120
when we won Round Two.

1456
01:31:31,120 --> 01:31:34,023
It's Team A Gloomy Day. Congratulations.

1457
01:31:34,023 --> 01:31:40,728
(They shed joyful tears
with their teammates.)

1458
01:31:42,565 --> 01:31:46,502
The hours the News Anchor Who Bakes
quietly spent baking.

1459
01:31:47,837 --> 01:31:50,673
(No one noticed her,)

1460
01:31:50,673 --> 01:31:55,542
(but she put her whole heart into baking.)

1461
01:31:56,846 --> 01:31:58,381
The disappointment of being eliminated.

1462
01:31:58,915 --> 01:32:02,285
The heartache of having to say goodbye
to teammates.

1463
01:32:03,361 --> 01:32:04,418
Thank you.

1464
01:32:05,221 --> 01:32:07,690
Please leave the pastry factory.

1465
01:32:09,625 --> 01:32:11,892
Tears of happiness from passing.

1466
01:32:12,428 --> 01:32:15,198
I wanted to put the emotions I felt...

1467
01:32:15,798 --> 01:32:18,501
from seeing all our tears and passion...

1468
01:32:18,801 --> 01:32:21,837
in this water drop-shaped pastry.

1469
01:32:22,438 --> 01:32:25,408
We fought fiercely in this competition,

1470
01:32:25,641 --> 01:32:29,812
but before that, we were comrades
walking the same path.

1471
01:32:34,450 --> 01:32:38,321
We put our everyday work on hold
to be here,

1472
01:32:38,688 --> 01:32:42,058
and after the competition,
we went back to work and baked.

1473
01:32:42,325 --> 01:32:46,395
Bakers are up earlier than anyone else.

1474
01:32:47,096 --> 01:32:51,167
People around the world are
giving their all for their dreams.

1475
01:32:51,884 --> 01:32:56,282
I put the tears and passion
of those people in Si Yeop's Dream.

1476
01:32:57,640 --> 01:33:00,076
It holds the tears and effort...

1477
01:33:00,076 --> 01:33:02,111
of everyone chasing their dreams.

1478
01:33:02,445 --> 01:33:05,815
That's the pastry that I think
will take over the world.

1479
01:33:08,951 --> 01:33:10,620
That's so touching.

1480
01:33:10,620 --> 01:33:11,621
That's cool.

1481
01:33:11,888 --> 01:33:13,556
I got goosebumps.

1482
01:33:13,556 --> 01:33:15,024
I know. That was incredible.

1483
01:33:19,328 --> 01:33:20,563
Si Yeop is cool!

1484
01:33:20,563 --> 01:33:23,366
I didn't expect this many bakers
to come for me.

1485
01:33:24,367 --> 01:33:27,136
They all came for me as a surprise.

1486
01:33:27,436 --> 01:33:29,205
That was unexpected.

1487
01:33:29,772 --> 01:33:31,274
Thank you.

1488
01:33:31,274 --> 01:33:33,570
(He gets emotional
thinking back on the journey.)

1489
01:33:33,576 --> 01:33:36,111
(Si Yeop, good luck! Today is your day!)

1490
01:33:36,112 --> 01:33:38,846
He got emotional.

1491
01:33:39,916 --> 01:33:43,553
(Si Yeop's Dream holds tears and passion.)

1492
01:33:43,854 --> 01:33:46,122
Here's how to eat Si Yeop's Dream.

1493
01:33:46,356 --> 01:33:48,824
Cut the pastry diagonally along the line.

1494
01:33:48,925 --> 01:33:52,295
The right side has pistachio cream,

1495
01:33:52,929 --> 01:33:56,032
and the left side has Udo peanut cream.

1496
01:33:56,499 --> 01:33:58,935
Take a bite of the smooth pistachio first,

1497
01:33:58,935 --> 01:34:00,803
then the nutty Udo peanut cream,

1498
01:34:00,803 --> 01:34:02,939
and after that, enjoy them together.

1499
01:34:41,543 --> 01:34:45,214
Masters, please share your thoughts
on the pastry.

1500
01:34:45,816 --> 01:34:49,785
Your presentation really touched my heart.

1501
01:34:49,785 --> 01:34:52,188
After all the passion,

1502
01:34:52,188 --> 01:34:55,992
tears, and aspirations of so many people,

1503
01:34:55,992 --> 01:34:59,495
we made it to the Top 7 finals
in just 5 rounds.

1504
01:35:00,062 --> 01:35:02,265
People might laugh at this comment,

1505
01:35:03,165 --> 01:35:06,266
but I think it needed more salt...

1506
01:35:06,735 --> 01:35:09,236
to perfect this brand.

1507
01:35:09,639 --> 01:35:14,210
Compared to the presentation,
it's too sweet and happy.

1508
01:35:14,537 --> 01:35:17,413
From both a taste
and marketing perspective,

1509
01:35:17,413 --> 01:35:20,216
adding a bit of salt
to the peanut cream...

1510
01:35:20,216 --> 01:35:23,553
would have balanced it better
with the pistachio...

1511
01:35:23,553 --> 01:35:26,589
and made the flavor perfectly
match the story.

1512
01:35:26,589 --> 01:35:29,892
I thought the flavor could've been better.

1513
01:35:29,992 --> 01:35:31,794
I agree with Master Hee Young.

1514
01:35:31,794 --> 01:35:36,065
I also thought
that if you added more salt,

1515
01:35:36,065 --> 01:35:41,238
it would've made the pastry more special.

1516
01:35:41,238 --> 01:35:44,073
Still, the technique was perfect,

1517
01:35:44,073 --> 01:35:47,510
the work was flawless,
and the presentation was spot-on.

1518
01:35:47,510 --> 01:35:49,111
Great job today.

1519
01:35:49,712 --> 01:35:51,514
That comment was accurate.

1520
01:35:51,714 --> 01:35:55,618
It's too savory and not salty enough,

1521
01:35:55,818 --> 01:35:57,787
which makes it taste a bit bland.

1522
01:35:58,020 --> 01:36:00,623
Master Julian, what did you think?

1523
01:36:00,623 --> 01:36:03,259
Technically, it's very well-done.

1524
01:36:03,726 --> 01:36:06,262
When you were cutting the dough...

1525
01:36:06,262 --> 01:36:08,264
with the stencil method,

1526
01:36:08,264 --> 01:36:12,335
we were wondering what it was going to be
and how it would look.

1527
01:36:12,435 --> 01:36:17,473
I think it came out super impressive
for the presentation!

1528
01:36:20,443 --> 01:36:23,913
The shape is phenomenal.
It just shines through...

1529
01:36:23,913 --> 01:36:25,848
just like a museum piece.

1530
01:36:27,283 --> 01:36:31,120
I think it was really smart
how you divided the dessert...

1531
01:36:31,120 --> 01:36:33,689
into two halves for the different flavors.

1532
01:36:33,689 --> 01:36:35,124
It made it kind of dynamic.

1533
01:36:35,124 --> 01:36:38,394
You could try one side first
and then the other.

1534
01:36:38,394 --> 01:36:41,797
It was very well executed
and really enjoyable to eat.

1535
01:36:41,864 --> 01:36:43,299
Nothing to point out.

1536
01:36:43,699 --> 01:36:44,765
Thank you.

1537
01:36:46,102 --> 01:36:48,871
"I did better than I thought.
Did I nail it?"

1538
01:36:49,005 --> 01:36:51,741
"It's not bad." That's what I thought.

1539
01:36:52,975 --> 01:36:56,879
Si Yeop, the final judging is over.

1540
01:36:57,079 --> 01:36:59,047
